      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A pathogen category referenced through cited work on airborne virus transmission via respiratory droplets and short-range exposure. In the excerpt, these larger-droplet transmission mechanisms were not evaluated because only smaller aerosols under 3 µm were generated. | A generic airborne viral pathogen referenced through cited work on sneezing and asymptomatic virus transmission. The excerpt implies that respiratory droplets may act as carriers for viral transmission, but it does not identify a specific virus. | A generalized airborne viral pathogen referenced in the context of short-range airborne transmission. Exposure risk depends on respiratory particle dynamics, suspension time, evaporation, and local airflow.</data>
