      <data key="d0">BIOAEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Biological aerosol particles mentioned in the context of staff exposure in a dental office. The excerpt does not specify organism type, infectivity, concentration, ventilation conditions, or containment controls. | Airborne biological particles studied as contaminants of concern in the subway compartment. The experiment showed that they could spread rapidly through the air and also deposit on contact surfaces such as the ground, seats, and windows. | Airborne biological particles emitted during respiratory activities such as breathing, speaking, and coughing. In infection-control contexts, such aerosols may carry pathogens.</data>
