      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">ICU rooms maintained under positive pressure relative to surrounding areas; evaluated for aerosol decay rates, spatial distribution patterns, and potential aerosol exfiltration. | A clinical room operated under positive pressure; it allowed up to 6% aerosol escape and cleared aerosols more slowly than negative-pressure ICUs.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.91</data>
      <data key="d4">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_18</data>
