      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">ICU rooms with neutral pressure relative to adjacent spaces; used as a comparison condition for aerosol persistence, decay, and distribution behavior. | Clinical rooms operated without a strong positive or negative pressure bias; they allowed up to 19% aerosol escape, the highest leakage reported among the pressure conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.91</data>
      <data key="d4">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_18</data>
