    <node id="OPERATING ROOM">
      <data key="d0">OPERATING ROOM</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">A surgical clinical zone discussed as the setting for CFD analysis and sensor-network measurement of airflow and aerosol transport. The text emphasizes that operating-room dimensions, temperature, personnel movement, layout, air handling, and positive pressure influence aerosol distribution and leakage. | A controlled clinical zone referenced in a study predicting concentrations of exhaled-aerosol exposure among healthcare workers. It is important because operating-room airflow affects contaminant distribution and staff exposure. | The clinical surgical environment used as the simulation setting for standing and lying human manikins. The operating room context is relevant because thermal assumptions, buoyancy-driven airflow, leakage paths, and particle transport can affect contaminant dispersion in a controlled healthcare zone.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_37,62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_39,62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_51,62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d5">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1,c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b,6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
      <data key="d6">OPERATING ROOM</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LARGER MODERN OPERATING ROOMS">
      <data key="d0">LARGER MODERN OPERATING ROOMS</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">A subgroup of operating rooms described as larger and more modern. In these rooms, the aerosol plume did not reach the room perimeter because the air handling scheme was effective.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SMALLER OPERATING ROOMS">
      <data key="d0">SMALLER OPERATING ROOMS</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">Smaller operating-room spaces whose aerosol behavior was reported to resemble that observed in the current ICU study. Their behavior supports the point that room size and layout strongly affect aerosol distribution.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </node>
