      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Potentially infectious airborne particles discussed in relation to persistence in dental offices and aerosol behavior in medical facilities. | Pathogen-bearing airborne particles identified as the transmission concern in venue ventilation studies. Their concentration and distribution depend on source occupants, ventilation concept, and air distribution behavior. | Aerosolized infectious particles identified as potential products or transported material associated with sneezing, breathing, and other pulmonary bioaerosol sources. | Airborne infectious particles whose spread and exposure were evaluated under VV1 and VV2 ventilation strategies.</data>
