    </node>
    <node id="VENTILATION FLOW RATE">
      <data key="d0">VENTILATION FLOW RATE</data>
      <data key="d1">ACH_RATE</data>
      <data key="d2">The rate of supplied or exhausted ventilation airflow discussed as a factor affecting room aerosol behavior. Although not expressed as a numeric air-change-per-hour value in the text, it functions as the ventilation-rate parameter influencing aerosol distribution. | A ventilation-rate factor identified as affecting indoor tracer-gas and aerosol-particle distributions; no specific numerical air-change rate is provided in the text. | The amount of ventilation or fresh-air supply considered in the high-speed train study. Although reported as air-supply or fresh-air volume rather than explicitly as ACH, it functions as the ventilation-rate variable in the schema; doubling it produced similar removal trends but stabilized large vortices and increased particle capture and retention.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_39</data>
