    <node id="INDOOR AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d0">INDOOR AIRFLOW</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Indoor airflow is identified as a factor influencing the evaporation rate of respiratory particles by affecting the vapour pressure difference between particle surfaces and ambient air. | The internal cabin airflow pathway that transports bioaerosols longitudinally through the cabin and, after release cessation, carries a substantial portion of bacteria into the external cabin environment.</data>
