    <node id="NO-VENTILATION CASE">
      <data key="d0">NO-VENTILATION CASE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">The baseline air-distribution condition in which no active mechanical ventilation is applied, used to compare CO2 accumulation and droplet persistence against fan-driven cases. | Scenario with no active ventilation or fan-driven airflow. It was least effective at exhausting CO2, reaching 35 ppm in 15 seconds, and was associated with a higher contagion rate; however, for liquid droplet dispersion it appeared safest because droplets fell downward and evaporated before reaching the floor.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.91</data>
      <data key="d4">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
