      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">A ventilation strategy in which the ceiling fan blows downward into the lift, producing a different airflow pattern that affects CO2 distribution, droplet removal, and exposure conditions. | Ventilation airflow configuration in which air is blown downward. It is compared with no-fan and upward-blowing cases to evaluate droplet dispersion under different ventilation strategies.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.91</data>
      <data key="d4">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
