      <data key="d2">An occupied indoor room studied for ventilation efficiency, infectious-disease transmission reduction, thermal comfort, and CO2-level reduction. Although not a clinical room, it is a room-scale indoor zone where airflow, ventilation, and exposure control are evaluated. | An occupied indoor room discussed in a cited study of indoor climate using mixing and displacement air distribution methods. Although the text is not specifically about a hospital, this is the closest available zone-type category for the studied indoor space. | An indoor classroom modeled in digital-twin and CFD case studies of respiratory aerosol transport. It is treated as a zone because the text discusses room-scale ventilation, occupant exposure, and particle distribution in a space occupied by students and a teacher.</data>
