      <data key="d0">CO2</data>
      <data key="d1">TRACER_GAS</data>
      <data key="d2">Carbon dioxide referenced in a classroom study of thermal comfort and CO2-level reduction. CO2 is relevant as an indoor-air indicator and commonly used surrogate for ventilation effectiveness and occupant-generated air accumulation. | Carbon dioxide used as an indicator or tracer gas in high-resolution theatre monitoring. Occupant-generated CO2 provides evidence of ventilation effectiveness and dilution during events with spectators. | Tracer gas emitted by all virtual spectators as part of breathing air at 20 litres per hour per spectator. Its movement was modeled as dependent on room air flow and used as an indicator of air movement and exposure-relevant transport.</data>
