      <data key="d0">HEALTHY PASSENGER RESPIRATION VOLUME</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Breathing-zone volume associated with the healthy passenger. It is used to evaluate whether recirculated droplets or contaminants enter the susceptible passenger's inhalation region.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.79</data>
      <data key="d4">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d5">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HEALTHY PASSENGER">
      <data key="d0">HEALTHY PASSENGER</data>
      <data key="d1">OCCUPANCY_LOAD</data>
      <data key="d2">Susceptible standing occupant in the lift model. The passenger's position and respiration volume are used to judge whether direct contagion or exposure to recirculated droplets occurs under each ventilation scenario.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.83</data>
      <data key="d4">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d5">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STANDARD-SIZE MODELLED ROOM">
      <data key="d0">STANDARD-SIZE MODELLED ROOM</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">Indoor standard-size modelled occupied zone containing two standing subjects. It was the simulation space where CO2 concentration, cough-particle removal, and liquid droplet dispersion were compared under no ventilation, upward-blowing fan, and downward-blowing fan cases.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
