      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">A ventilation air-distribution condition abbreviated as DF. It describes downward-directed airflow, which is relevant for evaluating how supplied air transports or dilutes airborne contaminants and tracer gases. | A ventilation air-distribution condition abbreviated as UF. It describes upward-directed airflow, which may affect vertical transport, dilution, and removal of airborne contaminants or tracer gases.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.74</data>
      <data key="d4">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_42</data>
