      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">An airborne infection-risk metric implied by the listed quanta emission rate q and probability of risk of infection P. It represents pathogen-bearing infectious dose units used in airborne transmission modeling. | The airborne infectious dose metric used to quantify aerosol exposure. Concentrations of infectious quanta in occupants' breathing zones were used to calculate individual and global infection risks.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
