    </node>
    <node id="INDOOR ENVIRONMENT">
      <data key="d0">INDOOR ENVIRONMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">A generic indoor room or zone referenced in studies of decontamination and airborne droplet transport after sneezing; no specific hospital area is identified in the text. | An indoor modeled zone referenced in the numerical study involving a ceiling fan and an upper-room ultraviolet germicidal irradiation system. It represents the enclosed space where airflow, mixing, and pathogen-related exposure conditions are assessed. | A generic indoor occupied space discussed as the setting where respiratory aerosols may sediment onto surfaces or remain suspended and disseminate depending on airflow conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_46</data>
