      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The infection risk assessed in Spanish secondary school and university classrooms. Although SARS-CoV-2 is not explicitly named in the excerpt, the COVID-19 risk is tied to airborne exposure and indoor air-quality conditions. | COVID-19 is the infectious disease context in which aerosol particles expelled during singing and speaking are treated as a potential airborne transmission pathway.</data>
