      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Airborne infectious aerosols represent pathogen-bearing respiratory particles associated with COVID-19 infection risk in the cited indoor-environment studies. The text focuses on aerosol-mediated infection risk rather than direct pathogen measurement. | A generic airborne infectious aerosol hazard referenced in relation to cough-release transmission and mitigation by ventilation, air change rate, and air distribution system performance. | General airborne infectious material implied by the cited study on infection dynamics affected by leakage through N95 respirators.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
