    <node id="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19">
      <data key="d0">SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">COVID-19 is referenced as the pandemic context for indoor air-quality evaluation in a ventilated fitness center. In this extraction it represents SARS-CoV-2-related airborne infectious risk in indoor environments. | Referenced through the article title 'Event-specific interventions to minimize COVID-19 transmission.' In this extraction it is represented as the airborne or aerosol-transmissible infectious agent associated with COVID-19 transmission risk. | COVID-19 is referenced through a cited outbreak associated with air conditioning in a restaurant in Guangzhou, China. In this ventilation and airflow context, it represents the airborne infectious hazard of concern, most directly corresponding to SARS-CoV-2 transmission risk. | COVID-19 is referenced in relation to indoor infection risk reduction; the domain-relevant airborne pathogen is SARS-CoV-2, the virus responsible for COVID-19. | The airborne infectious hazard discussed in the context of mass gatherings, aerosol exposure, masks, ventilation, and epidemic spread. Transmission risk is described as being strongly influenced by ventilation adequacy and occupancy/contact conditions. | Referenced through COVID-19 as the infectious disease context for potential aerosol-based transmission during singing and speaking.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.94</data>
      <data key="d4">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_53</data>
      <data key="d5">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b,2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206,6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42,d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff,0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d,ffb605c7-88bd-433a-9478-a7261e327d48</data>
      <data key="d6">SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19,SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIRBORNE AND DROPLET TRANSMISSION PATHWAYS">
      <data key="d0">AIRBORNE AND DROPLET TRANSMISSION PATHWAYS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Airborne and droplet transmission pathways are referenced in the cited article on predicting infection probability distributions. These pathways describe routes by which infectious respiratory emissions may move through indoor air and contribute to exposure. | The text references airborne and aerosol routes as pathways by which SARS-CoV-2 may be transmitted through air, including evidence, prevention, and control considerations. | The text identifies an airborne transmission route involving aerosol particles sized 0.1–10 μm and larger droplets sized ≥10 μm. These particles can carry virus between emitter and receiver; larger ejected droplets are described as moving ballistically under momentum, initial direction, and gravity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_53</data>
      <data key="d5">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b,0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d,ffb605c7-88bd-433a-9478-a7261e327d48</data>
      <data key="d6">AIRBORNE AND AEROSOL TRANSMISSION PATHWAY,AEROSOL AND DROPLET TRANSMISSION PATHWAY</data>
    </node>
