    <node id="TURBULENT GAS CLOUDS">
      <data key="d0">TURBULENT GAS CLOUDS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Turbulent gas clouds describe the exhaled airflow pattern associated with respiratory emissions. This distribution pattern can carry pathogen-laden aerosols and influence short-range airborne transmission. | Turbulent gas clouds are described as a respiratory-flow phenomenon associated with pathogen emissions. They represent a dynamic air distribution pattern that can influence how exhaled particles and pathogens disperse.</data>
