      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Airborne virus-bearing respiratory particles transported in the enclosed elevator environment and associated with infection-risk evaluation. | Aerosolized virus-containing particles generated, UV-exposed, transported, and collected within the one-pass exposure system. The aerosol size distribution was typical of human coughing, breathing, and talking, with over 90% of particles less than 1.0 µm in diameter.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
