      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">The occupied seating zone where the study design places one infectious person within a fully occupied audience. It is a key exposure zone for assessing airborne transmission risk in venues.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_48</data>
      <data key="d5">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HIGHLY EXPOSED POSITIONS">
      <data key="d0">HIGHLY EXPOSED POSITIONS</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">Specific occupied positions in the venue where aerosol exposure may be elevated. The text notes that identifying such positions is difficult because room airflow depends strongly on boundary conditions and room parameters.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_48</data>
