      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A pathogenic microorganism named as a UV-LED inactivation target in the cited Water Research study. Although the cited context is water disinfection, Pseudomonas aeruginosa can be associated with healthcare environments and may become aerosolized from contaminated water sources, making it potentially relevant to airborne exposure control.</data>
