      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Three-dimensional turbulent airflow pattern produced by the coach ventilation. This pattern governs the modeled transport and dispersion of emitted particles ranging from 1 µm to 1 mm in aerodynamic diameter. | The turbulent air distribution pattern created by ventilation and modeled using Eulerian and Lagrangian CFD approaches. It governs the transport and dispersion of suspended aerosols and larger droplets in semi-confined ventilated spaces.</data>
