      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Liquid respiratory particles emitted by the infected passenger and carrying infectious biological agents. The modeled particle size range spans approximately 1 µm to 1 mm, with smaller droplets associated with breathing and larger drops associated with coughing. | Potentially infectious respiratory particles emitted during coughing and talking in the Covid-19 transmission scenario. The modeled particle ranges were approximately 0.3–1000 µm for coughing and 0.3–10 µm for talking.</data>
