      <data key="d0">COVID-19 VIRIONS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Example pathogen described as being contained in emitted respiratory particles. The text uses COVID-19 virions as an illustrative infectious agent whose particle-borne dispersion may be modeled in the railway coach. | A specific airborne pathogen mentioned as a biological component that could be integrated into the dispersion model. The text refers to estimating virion load, inhaled virion number, and changes in pathogenicity during aerial transport or after particle deposition. | An airborne viral pathogen referenced in the context of respiratory droplet and aerosol transmission in indoor spaces, where persistence and dissemination may be shaped by airflow and environmental conditions.</data>
