      <data key="d0">POTENTIALLY INFECTIOUS DROPLET PARTICLES FROM 1 ΜM TO 1 MM</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The modeled respiratory particle size range, spanning small aerosol droplets suspended in air and larger drops that fall or behave like projectiles depending on initial velocity. These particles represent the contamination-bearing material whose dispersion is evaluated.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_1</data>
      <data key="d5">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SURGICAL MASK FILTRATION AIR PATH">
      <data key="d0">SURGICAL MASK FILTRATION AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The airflow route through a surgical mask, modeled as a filtration pathway that can reduce droplet and aerosol release from occupants when masks are worn properly.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.72</data>
      <data key="d4">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_1</data>
      <data key="d5">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LOOSE-MASK LEAKAGE AIR PATHS">
      <data key="d0">LOOSE-MASK LEAKAGE AIR PATHS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Bypass airflow paths around a poorly adjusted surgical mask. These leaks allow respiratory particles to escape around the mask and alter the resulting airborne particle distribution. | The leakage paths around a loosely fitted mask where spaces exist between the face and the mask. These paths allow air and particles to bypass the filtering part while still limiting overall droplet dissemination compared with no-mask conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_1</data>
