      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Spatial distribution pattern of droplets and drops carrying infectious agents, studied using physical modelling and numerical simulation. | Respiratory droplet turbulent dispersion is the airflow-driven transport of respiratory droplets in a ventilated city bus, studied using high-performance CFD. | Respiratory tract droplets disperse through exhaled airflow; the cited studies examine dispersion during speech, vocal exercises, and with face coverings.</data>
