    <node id="MASKED DROPLET DISPERSION PATTERN">
      <data key="d0">MASKED DROPLET DISPERSION PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">The resulting dispersion pattern of droplets and particles emitted by the infected passenger when masks are worn. The study found limited dissemination within the railway coach for both tightly fitted and poorly fitted masks. | Observed/simulated spatial distribution of respiratory droplets for the perfectly fitting surgical-mask case. The pattern is visualized over time in the symmetry plane of the manikin and reflects reduced droplet release due to an assumed 75% mask filtration efficiency, with some droplets re-aspirated and removed from the computation. | Pattern of airborne transport and spread of droplets released during sneezing, studied through experiments and transient CFD modeling in indoor environments.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_5</data>
