      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">Ventilation configurations used in conventional indoor environments where air is supplied and exhausted through designated pathways. The text contrasts these systems with the more complex subway-cabin circulation mode.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.72</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR SUPPLY-RETURN SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">AIR SUPPLY-RETURN SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">Ventilation configurations used in conventional indoor environments where supplied air is partly returned through return pathways. These systems are contrasted with combined supply-return-exhaust circulation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.72</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
