      <data key="d0">COMBINED AIR SUPPLY-RETURN-EXHAUST CIRCULATION MODE</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">A ventilation configuration typically used in subway cabins that integrates supply, return, and exhaust airflow. The text states that this mode reduces fan noise, saves energy, maintains passenger comfort, and can create extremely complex cabin airflow patterns.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_5</data>
