      <data key="d0">AIR CONDITIONING RECIRCULATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">The recirculating airflow condition produced by the subway cabin air-conditioning system. It is explicitly considered in the experimental setup because it can influence bioaerosol mixing, transport, and propagation inside the cabin.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_9,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR CONDITIONING CYCLES">
      <data key="d0">AIR CONDITIONING CYCLES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Operational airflow cycling of the subway cabin air-conditioning system. The study accounts for these cycles when assessing how bioaerosols propagate under realistic subway operating conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR DUCT STRUCTURE">
      <data key="d0">AIR DUCT STRUCTURE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The physical duct configuration of the subway cabin ventilation system. It forms part of the cabin air path and affects how supplied or recirculated air moves through the cabin, thereby influencing bioaerosol distribution.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_9,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FULLY ENCLOSED SUBWAY OPERATIONAL CONDITION">
      <data key="d0">FULLY ENCLOSED SUBWAY OPERATIONAL CONDITION</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">A subway cabin operational scenario in which the cabin is fully enclosed. The study evaluates bioaerosol propagation under this condition as one of the relevant airflow and containment settings. | A subway cabin operational scenario in which the cabin is semi-enclosed. This condition is compared with fully enclosed operation to understand changes in bioaerosol propagation behavior.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.72</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
      <data key="d6">SEMI-ENCLOSED SUBWAY OPERATIONAL CONDITION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BIOAEROSOL PROPAGATION MODES">
      <data key="d0">BIOAEROSOL PROPAGATION MODES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Observed or inferred movement and distribution patterns of bioaerosols inside the subway cabin under different operational and ventilation conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.83</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBWAY CABIN LABORATORY">
      <data key="d0">SUBWAY CABIN LABORATORY</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">A full-scale enclosed experimental subway-cabin mockup used as the controlled occupied zone for studying aerosolized pathogen transmission. It reproduces an authentic cabin geometry with dimensions of 17.34 m × 2.58 m × 2.35 m and includes interior elements such as windows, doors, seating units, vertical supports, insulated walls, floor, and ceiling.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.96</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DUCT SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">DUCT SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The comprehensive ducted airflow network installed in the subway cabin laboratory. Its physical structure provides airflow pathways between the ventilation system and the cabin and is a practical factor affecting aerosol transport.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIVERSE VENTILATION APPROACHES">
      <data key="d0">DIVERSE VENTILATION APPROACHES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">The different ventilation modes or airflow strategies evaluated in the subway cabin laboratory to determine how ventilation configuration and operating conditions affect aerosol transmission.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AEROSOLIZED PATHOGEN">
      <data key="d0">AEROSOLIZED PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The airborne biological contaminant or pathogen-bearing aerosol whose transmission characteristics inside the subway cabin are investigated using a combined microbiological and engineering approach.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBWAY CABIN">
      <data key="d0">SUBWAY CABIN</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">The occupied compartment of the experimental subway train laboratory whose ventilation behavior is described. It receives treated supply air from the air conditioning units, returns part of its air for recirculation, and exhausts the remaining air to the outdoor environment. | Indoor occupied transport compartment used as the modeled zone for pollutant dispersion and infection-risk prediction. Classified under the closest available zone type.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_20,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_25,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_28,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_34</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
      <data key="d6">SUBWAY CAR CABIN</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TWO AIR CONDITIONING UNITS">
      <data key="d0">TWO AIR CONDITIONING UNITS</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">The two HVAC units that treat air before delivery to the subway cabin. They receive return air from the cabin, mix it with fresh air, and recirculate conditioned air through the supply system. Their operation can be adjusted through an intelligent control cabinet.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INTELLIGENT CONTROL CABINET">
      <data key="d0">INTELLIGENT CONTROL CABINET</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">The control component associated with the air conditioning units. It enables multiple ventilation modes, including external circulation and internal circulation, and supports air-supply frequency modulation in the 30–50 Hz range.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUPPLY AIR DUCTS">
      <data key="d0">SUPPLY AIR DUCTS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Air conveyance paths that carry treated air from the air conditioning units toward the supply air grilles before it enters the subway cabin.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ROOF SUPPLY AIR GRILLES">
      <data key="d0">ROOF SUPPLY AIR GRILLES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Roof-mounted supply openings through which treated air enters the subway cabin from above. They implement the top-air-supply portion of the ventilation pattern.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RETURN AIR INLETS">
      <data key="d0">RETURN AIR INLETS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Return openings that draw a portion of cabin air back toward the air conditioning units. The returned air mixes with fresh air and is then recirculated into the cabin.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXHAUST AIR DUCTS">
      <data key="d0">EXHAUST AIR DUCTS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Exhaust conveyance paths that remove the non-returned portion of cabin air from the compartment and direct it toward exhaust outlets.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXHAUST AIR OUTLETS">
      <data key="d0">EXHAUST AIR OUTLETS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Terminal exhaust openings through which part of the cabin air is discharged directly into the external environment.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FRESH AIR PATH">
      <data key="d0">FRESH AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The outdoor-air intake path that supplies fresh air to the air conditioning units, where it mixes with return air before being supplied back to the cabin.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXTERNAL ENVIRONMENT">
      <data key="d0">EXTERNAL ENVIRONMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">The outdoor environment outside the subway cabin. It provides fresh air during external circulation operation and receives discharged exhaust air through the exhaust outlets. | The environment outside the subway cabin that receives a significant portion of airborne bacteria carried out of the cabin by indoor airflow after bioaerosol release stops.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.74</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_21</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
      <data key="d6">EXTERNAL CABIN ENVIRONMENT</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TOP AIR SUPPLY-TOP AIR RETURN-BOTTOM AIR EXHAUST CONFIGURATION">
      <data key="d0">TOP AIR SUPPLY-TOP AIR RETURN-BOTTOM AIR EXHAUST CONFIGURATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">The standard ventilation configuration used in the experimental subway cabin. Air is supplied from the top, returned from the top, and exhausted from the bottom. The text states that this pattern helps expel heat and pollutants and provides favorable energy-efficiency and thermal-comfort performance.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.94</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXTERNAL CIRCULATION OPERATION">
      <data key="d0">EXTERNAL CIRCULATION OPERATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">A selectable ventilation operating mode in which air exchange occurs between the indoor cabin and the outdoor environment. It is enabled by the air conditioning control system and can operate with air-supply frequency modulation. | A selectable ventilation operating mode in which there is no air exchange between the indoor cabin and outdoor environment. It emphasizes recirculation of cabin air through the air conditioning units.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.67</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
      <data key="d6">INTERNAL CIRCULATION OPERATION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OVERALL SUPPLY AIR VOLUME OF 8500 M3/H">
      <data key="d0">OVERALL SUPPLY AIR VOLUME OF 8500 M3/H</data>
      <data key="d1">ACH_RATE</data>
      <data key="d2">The total supply airflow rate delivered to the cabin under the standard ventilation mode, reported as 8,500 m³/h.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FRESH AIR VOLUME OF 2600 M3/H">
      <data key="d0">FRESH AIR VOLUME OF 2600 M3/H</data>
      <data key="d1">ACH_RATE</data>
      <data key="d2">The fresh-air component of the total cabin supply airflow under the standard ventilation mode, reported as 2,600 m³/h.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.72</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RETURN AIR VOLUME OF 5900 M3/H">
      <data key="d0">RETURN AIR VOLUME OF 5900 M3/H</data>
      <data key="d1">ACH_RATE</data>
      <data key="d2">The recirculated return-air component of the total cabin supply airflow under the standard ventilation mode, reported as 5,900 m³/h.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.72</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CABIN">
      <data key="d0">CABIN</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">An enclosed experimental indoor zone served by a controlled ventilation and air-conditioning system. Under the described ventilation mode, it receives a total supply airflow of 8,500 m³/h, consisting of 2,600 m³/h fresh air and 5,900 m³/h return air.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_12,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_21</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUPPLY AIR PATH">
      <data key="d0">SUPPLY AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The total air-supply pathway delivering air into the cabin under the described ventilation mode. Its reported total flow rate is 8,500 m³/h.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RETURN AIR PATH">
      <data key="d0">RETURN AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The recirculated-air component of the cabin ventilation supply. It contributes 5,900 m³/h of return air to the total 8,500 m³/h supply airflow and is part of the cabin air-conditioning loop.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DESCRIBED VENTILATION MODE">
      <data key="d0">DESCRIBED VENTILATION MODE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">The ventilation operating condition described for the cabin, characterized by a total supply airflow of 8,500 m³/h made up of 2,600 m³/h fresh air and 5,900 m³/h return air.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STAPHYLOCOCCUS AUREUS">
      <data key="d0">STAPHYLOCOCCUS AUREUS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A biosafety level II organism used in indoor bioaerosol dispersion studies and air-purification testing. In the experiment, pure S. aureus cultures are grown in LB liquid medium at 37 °C and 150 r/min for 24 h, then diluted with phosphate-buffered saline to 10^6 cfu/ml as the aerosol generation solution.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="S. AUREUS BIOAEROSOL">
      <data key="d0">S. AUREUS BIOAEROSOL</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Staphylococcus aureus is diluted with phosphate-buffered saline to a final concentration of 10^6 cfu/ml and used as the pathogen-containing aerosol generation solution in the experiment.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_13,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STANDING PASSENGER MANIKIN">
      <data key="d0">STANDING PASSENGER MANIKIN</data>
      <data key="d1">OCCUPANCY_LOAD</data>
      <data key="d2">A manikin approximately 1.7 m tall represents a standing passenger and functions as a human-like occupant aerosol source connected to the aerosol generation system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NASAL RESPIRATORY RELEASE PATH">
      <data key="d0">NASAL RESPIRATORY RELEASE PATH</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The aerosol is routed through the manikin and released from the nasal region, creating an air path intended to simulate human breathing emission.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HUMAN-LIKE RESPIRATORY AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d0">HUMAN-LIKE RESPIRATORY AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">The experimental aerosol release is designed to resemble human respiratory emissions, with most generated particles predominantly within the 10 μm size range and with time-varying respiratory flow based on measured human breathing data.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="S. AUREUS">
      <data key="d0">S. AUREUS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">S. aureus is the biological aerosol/pathogen collected and quantified in the experiment. Its airborne concentration is monitored with Andersen six-stage air samplers, and its surface deposition is observed using Columbia blood agar plates placed on compartment surfaces such as windows and seats.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_14,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_26,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_27,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBWAY CABIN / COMPARTMENT">
      <data key="d0">SUBWAY CABIN / COMPARTMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">The subway cabin or experimental compartment is the enclosed occupied indoor zone where S. aureus bioaerosol transport, concentration variation, surface deposition, and pathogen disinfection are considered. Although it is not a hospital space, it is represented as a zone because the schema uses HOSPITAL_ZONE for enclosed indoor air environments.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR PURIFICATION DEVICE">
      <data key="d0">AIR PURIFICATION DEVICE</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">The air purification device is an engineered air-treatment unit intended for pathogen disinfection in occupied traffic environments such as subway cabins. It must operate under human-machine copresence conditions because passengers are frequently present. | Two air purification units that remained operational during case 3, case 4, and case 5, which were designed to evaluate the efficiency of purification devices in the subway compartment.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
      <data key="d6">TWO PURIFICATION DEVICES</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INDOOR TURBULENCE">
      <data key="d0">INDOOR TURBULENCE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Indoor turbulence is the airflow distribution condition inside the compartment that influences how small-diameter S. aureus particles move through the air and deposit onto surfaces such as windows and seats.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RESPIRATORY-LIKE BIOAEROSOL EMISSION FLOW">
      <data key="d0">RESPIRATORY-LIKE BIOAEROSOL EMISSION FLOW</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">The respiratory-like bioaerosol emission flow is the simulated breathing emission pattern generated by the aerosol generator/manikin. The flow curve resembles human respiratory activity, with repeated breathing actions separated by a 0.2 s interval.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PASSENGER OCCUPANCY IN TRAFFIC ENVIRONMENTS">
      <data key="d0">PASSENGER OCCUPANCY IN TRAFFIC ENVIRONMENTS</data>
      <data key="d1">OCCUPANCY_LOAD</data>
      <data key="d2">Passenger occupancy represents the recurring human presence in traffic environments that motivates pathogen disinfection and human-compatible operation of air purification devices. Passenger presence is relevant because human respiratory activity is a source context for bioaerosol emissions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TRAIN CARRIAGES">
      <data key="d0">TRAIN CARRIAGES</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">Occupied train carriage spaces, especially crowded during peak times, where stable air intake, good air circulation, and ventilation are needed in confined passenger environments.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.87</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PASSENGER TRAFFIC ENVIRONMENTS">
      <data key="d0">PASSENGER TRAFFIC ENVIRONMENTS</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">Transportation environments characterized by frequent passenger presence, motivating air purification devices that can operate safely with humans nearby.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="IFD FILTER">
      <data key="d0">IFD FILTER</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">The first designed purification device using intense field dielectric technology with dielectric materials as the medium; selected for low air resistance and compatibility with high airflow needs in train air-conditioning systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_19,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_30,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_31,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_34</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TRADITIONAL PHYSICAL-MECHANICAL FILTERS">
      <data key="d0">TRADITIONAL PHYSICAL-MECHANICAL FILTERS</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">Conventional filters that can capture fine particulates effectively but are described as often producing high air resistance that may reduce air-conditioning airflow efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.74</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR CONDITIONING UNITS">
      <data key="d0">AIR CONDITIONING UNITS</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">Cabin air-handling units included among the simultaneous targets for pathogen disinfection along with cabin airflow and air ducts.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CABIN AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d0">CABIN AIRFLOW</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Air movement pathway within the subway cabin and one of the simultaneous targets for pathogen disinfection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR DUCTS">
      <data key="d0">AIR DUCTS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Ducted air pathways associated with the cabin air-conditioning system and included as targets for simultaneous pathogen disinfection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_23,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_26,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR INTAKE">
      <data key="d0">AIR INTAKE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Pathway by which air enters the train air-conditioning system; stable and sufficient intake is emphasized as essential for circulation and ventilation inside carriages.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.83</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LOW AIR RESISTANCE">
      <data key="d0">LOW AIR RESISTANCE</data>
      <data key="d1">PRESSURE_RELATIONSHIP</data>
      <data key="d2">Pressure-flow characteristic of the IFD filter that allows a large volume of air to pass into the air-conditioning system with less obstruction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HIGH AIR RESISTANCE">
      <data key="d0">HIGH AIR RESISTANCE</data>
      <data key="d1">PRESSURE_RELATIONSHIP</data>
      <data key="d2">Pressure-flow drawback associated with many traditional physical-mechanical filters, potentially reducing overall airflow efficiency of the air-conditioning system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GREAT VOLUME OF AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d0">GREAT VOLUME OF AIRFLOW</data>
      <data key="d1">ACH_RATE</data>
      <data key="d2">High air throughput enabled by the low-resistance IFD filter, supporting air intake and ventilation needs in the train air-conditioning system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GOOD AIR CIRCULATION AND VENTILATION INSIDE THE CARRIAGE">
      <data key="d0">GOOD AIR CIRCULATION AND VENTILATION INSIDE THE CARRIAGE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Desired air movement and ventilation condition inside train carriages, dependent on stable and sufficient air intake and important for confined occupied spaces.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIRFLOW EFFICIENCY">
      <data key="d0">AIRFLOW EFFICIENCY</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Performance condition of the air-conditioning system related to how effectively air can move through the system; negatively affected by high filter resistance.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FREQUENT PRESENCE OF PASSENGERS">
      <data key="d0">FREQUENT PRESENCE OF PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d1">OCCUPANCY_LOAD</data>
      <data key="d2">Recurring human occupancy in traffic environments that creates a requirement for purification devices compatible with human-machine copresence.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PEAK TIMES">
      <data key="d0">PEAK TIMES</data>
      <data key="d1">OCCUPANCY_LOAD</data>
      <data key="d2">Periods of elevated passenger occupancy in train carriages, increasing the importance of stable air intake, circulation, and ventilation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.77</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DESIGNED IFD FILTER">
      <data key="d0">DESIGNED IFD FILTER</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">An installed air purification device used in the train air conditioning system. It removes large particles with a low-resistance filter, charges particles near pin electrodes, captures fine particulate matter using honeycomb-shaped dielectric microchannels and wrapped electrodes, and neutralizes bacteria and microorganisms on particulates. Its tested operational power is 12 W.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CP GENERATOR">
      <data key="d0">CP GENERATOR</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">An air purification device shown as part of the field installation with the IFD filter in the train air conditioning system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.94</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_16,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_30,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_31,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_34</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SEALED TRAIN CABIN">
      <data key="d0">SEALED TRAIN CABIN</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">The enclosed occupied indoor cabin environment whose air quality and cleanliness are maintained by the train air conditioning system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXTERNAL OPERATING ENVIRONMENT">
      <data key="d0">EXTERNAL OPERATING ENVIRONMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The outside environment connected to the sealed train cabin through the train air conditioning system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_16,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CABIN-TO-EXTERIOR AIR PATHWAY">
      <data key="d0">CABIN-TO-EXTERIOR AIR PATHWAY</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The airflow conduit formed by the air conditioning system between the sealed cabin and the external operating environment.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PARTICLE-ASSOCIATED BACTERIA AND MICROORGANISMS">
      <data key="d0">PARTICLE-ASSOCIATED BACTERIA AND MICROORGANISMS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Bacteria and microorganisms adhering to airborne particulates that can be neutralized by the strong electric field in the IFD filter, potentially reducing microbial growth on the filter surface.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SEALED CABIN">
      <data key="d0">SEALED CABIN</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">An enclosed conditioned indoor zone whose airflow quality and air cleanliness are maintained by ventilation and air-purification systems. Although described as a cabin rather than a hospital room, it functions as the occupied indoor space receiving air from the rooftop air conditioning unit.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CONDUIT LINKING THE SEALED CABIN WITH THE EXTERNAL OPERATING ENVIRONMENT">
      <data key="d0">CONDUIT LINKING THE SEALED CABIN WITH THE EXTERNAL OPERATING ENVIRONMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">A duct-like airflow path connecting the sealed cabin with the external operating environment. It supports air exchange and is described as important for maintaining indoor airflow quality and air cleanliness.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ROOFTOP AIR CONDITIONING UNIT">
      <data key="d0">ROOFTOP AIR CONDITIONING UNIT</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">The main rooftop HVAC unit serving the sealed cabin. It includes a mixing chamber where fresh and recirculated air streams merge before air is supplied toward the cabin.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.94</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MIXING CHAMBER">
      <data key="d0">MIXING CHAMBER</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">An internal airflow junction within the rooftop air conditioning unit where fresh air and recirculated air streams merge. It is the installation location of the IFD filter and therefore a key point for influencing air entering the cabin.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FRESH AIR STREAM">
      <data key="d0">FRESH AIR STREAM</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The incoming outdoor-air stream that enters the mixing chamber of the rooftop air conditioning unit and combines with recirculated air before being supplied toward the cabin.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RECIRCULATED AIR STREAM">
      <data key="d0">RECIRCULATED AIR STREAM</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The return-air stream from the conditioned environment that enters the mixing chamber and merges with the fresh air stream before further conditioning and purification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR ENTERING THE CABIN">
      <data key="d0">AIR ENTERING THE CABIN</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">The downstream supply airflow delivered toward the sealed cabin after the fresh and recirculated air streams merge in the rooftop unit's mixing chamber and pass the installed purification equipment.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COLD PLASMA GENERATOR">
      <data key="d0">COLD PLASMA GENERATOR</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">A second air-purification device using non-equilibrium gas discharge technology with insulating materials integrated into the discharge space. The tested device generates positive and negative ions during operation and is intended to purify air with energy-efficient, low-noise negative ion technology.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ENTIRE CABIN SPACE">
      <data key="d0">ENTIRE CABIN SPACE</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">Occupied rail-transit cabin volume intended to be filled with treated supply air containing positive and negative ions. It is typed as a zone because it is the main enclosed occupied space served by the ventilation and purification system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR CONDITIONING UNIT">
      <data key="d0">AIR CONDITIONING UNIT</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">Ventilation and conditioning equipment that contains the air supply chamber and distributes treated air toward the rail cabin and duct system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR SUPPLY CHAMBER">
      <data key="d0">AIR SUPPLY CHAMBER</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Supply-side airflow compartment within the air conditioning unit where the CP generator is installed so that generated ions enter the outgoing supply airflow.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AIR DUCT SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">AIR DUCT SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_PATH</data>
      <data key="d2">Ducted airflow network associated with the cabin ventilation system. The study aims to distribute positive and negative ions through this duct system as well as the cabin space.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE ION DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d0">POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE ION DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Target air treatment pattern in which positive and negative ions, reported at approximately 3.5-5 million ions/cm³ during operation, are distributed through the air supply chamber, duct system, and cabin space.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SEALED OZONE TEST CHAMBER">
      <data key="d0">SEALED OZONE TEST CHAMBER</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">Controlled enclosed test zone with dimensions of 0.5 m × 0.5 m × 0.5 m used to evaluate ozone emissions from the CP generator.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OZONE">
      <data key="d0">OZONE</data>
      <data key="d1">TRACER_GAS</data>
      <data key="d2">Measured gaseous byproduct used to evaluate air purification device safety. In the available schema it is represented as a tracer-gas-type measured gas, although the study treats it as an emission byproduct rather than an intentional tracer. | The gaseous air-quality constituent measured every 10 seconds during the test period. The text indicates that ozone concentration was not expected to measurably change because of the room's high air exchange rate.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18,92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e,d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
      <data key="d6">OZONE</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CP GENERATOR OZONE BUILDUP PATTERN">
      <data key="d0">CP GENERATOR OZONE BUILDUP PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Observed ozone concentration increase in the sealed chamber during CP generator operation. The chamber concentration rose by an average of 1.75 ppm over 10 minutes, corresponding to an estimated ozone emission rate of approximately 2.80 mg/h.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
