      <data key="d1">AIR_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d2">Ozone concentration measurement condition at the outlet of the duct equipped with the IFD filter, used to assess byproduct release from the IFD purification device.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LONG-TIME AND HIGH-DENSITY PASSENGER DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d0">LONG-TIME AND HIGH-DENSITY PASSENGER DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d1">OCCUPANCY_LOAD</data>
      <data key="d2">Rail-transit occupancy condition involving prolonged exposure and dense passenger presence. This condition increases the importance of controlling ozone and other byproducts from air purification devices.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ULTRAVIOLET LAMP AIR PURIFICATION DEVICE">
      <data key="d0">ULTRAVIOLET LAMP AIR PURIFICATION DEVICE</data>
      <data key="d1">HVAC_UNIT</data>
      <data key="d2">Example of an air purification device category noted as potentially unsuitable for high-density passenger environments because such devices may generate many byproducts.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.55</data>
      <data key="d4">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </node>
