      <data key="d0">OCCUPIED MOUSE-CAGE CLEANING ROOM</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">The specific occupied room within an animal-care facility where aerosolized murine norovirus was quantified. This was the primary real-world room-scale test zone for evaluating reduction of airborne infectious virus under ceiling-installed 222-nm far-UVC exposure, with uncertainties related to airflow patterns, virus residence time, and delivered dose.</data>
