      <data key="d0">ANIMAL-CARE FACILITY</data>
      <data key="d1">HOSPITAL_ZONE</data>
      <data key="d2">The larger facility setting that contains the occupied mouse-cage cleaning room used for the study. It provides the operational built-environment context for the occupied-room airborne virus reduction experiment. | Facilities containing the occupied mouse-cage cleaning rooms where airborne murine norovirus was detected at high levels. Although not a conventional hospital ward, this is the facility context for the indoor airborne-pathogen study.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.58</data>
      <data key="d4">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_0</data>
