      <data key="d10">The negative-pressure ICU is defined by a negative pressure relationship relative to adjacent spaces. | Negative pressure ICUs are characterized by a negative pressure relationship used for infection control. | The negative pressure ICUs were operated under a negative-pressure condition, meaning the room pressure was lower than adjacent spaces. | The negative pressure ICU was maintained at lower pressure than adjacent areas to support inward airflow and containment of aerosolized particles. | The negative pressure ICU is explicitly described as operating under negative pressure conditions. | The negative-pressure ICU has a negative-pressure relationship relative to surrounding areas, supporting directional airflow control and airborne containment. | The ICU is explicitly described as a negative pressure ICU, meaning it has a negative pressure relationship relative to surrounding spaces.</data>
