      <data key="d7">OPEN DOORWAY</data>
      <data key="d8">ICU</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The open doorway connects directly to the ICU and creates a larger transfer pathway than the under-door gap.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OPEN DOORWAY" target="ZONE IMMEDIATELY OUTSIDE THE ICU">
      <data key="d7">OPEN DOORWAY</data>
      <data key="d8">ZONE IMMEDIATELY OUTSIDE THE ICU</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The open doorway connects the ICU with the outside zone and was associated with the highest aerosol exfiltration, approximately 2.4–20.2%.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="TRACE NACL AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">TRACE NACL AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure contained the generated trace NaCl aerosols sufficiently that outside sensors did not register an aerosol spike.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="POTENTIALLY INFECTIOUS RESPIRATORY AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">POTENTIALLY INFECTIOUS RESPIRATORY AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">The negative-pressure result suggests containment relevance for potentially infectious respiratory aerosols in clinical settings.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="AIRBORNE PATHOGENS">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE PATHOGENS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure helps contain aerosol-borne pathogens by limiting outward spread from ICU spaces to surrounding hospital areas. | Negative pressure helps contain airborne pathogens by biasing airflow into the ICU and supporting removal through ventilation or extraction pathways.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="AIRBORNE SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Because airborne SARS-CoV-2 is an airborne pathogen relevant to COVID-19 hospital settings, negative pressure is an applicable containment strategy for SARS-CoV-2-laden aerosols.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="SEVERE ACUTE RESPIRATORY SYNDROME CORONAVIRUS 2">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">SEVERE ACUTE RESPIRATORY SYNDROME CORONAVIRUS 2</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure is relevant to containment of airborne pathogens such as severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2, although the text notes that aerosols may still persist for 20–30 minutes in negative-pressure ICUs.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="AEROSOL EXFILTRATION PATHWAY">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOL EXFILTRATION PATHWAY</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure can help contain aerosol movement by reducing exfiltration from ICU rooms into adjacent shared spaces.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="NACL AEROSOL SURROGATE PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">NACL AEROSOL SURROGATE PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">The negative-pressure condition was relevant to containment of the generated aerosol surrogate particles, potentially limiting their migration from the ICU into adjacent areas.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.74</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="AEROSOLIZED PARTICLES GENERATED IN ICU">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOLIZED PARTICLES GENERATED IN ICU</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure contained the aerosolized particles generated in the ICU, as outside monitoring did not detect aerosol concentration spikes.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.98</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="NO OUTSIDE AEROSOL SPIKE">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">NO OUTSIDE AEROSOL SPIKE</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure produced a containment pattern in which particles remained inside the room and no outside aerosol spike was detected.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.96</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="DOORS, DOOR GAPS, OR OTHER OPENINGS">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">DOORS, DOOR GAPS, OR OTHER OPENINGS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Under negative pressure, air enters the ICU through doors, door gaps, or openings, limiting outward aerosol movement and keeping Zone 3 PM near background.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="AEROSOLIZED PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOLIZED PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure contained aerosolized particles under closed-door experimental conditions, with no fugitive aerosols detected outside the ICU.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">In the COVID-19 ICU context, negative pressure supports containment of SARS-CoV-2-laden aerosols by reducing outward migration from the room.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="POTENTIALLY INFECTIOUS PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">POTENTIALLY INFECTIOUS PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure contained outward spread of potentially infectious particles by effectively eliminating aerosol leaks from ICUs, although it can also draw outside aerosol into the room.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="OUTSIDE-TO-ICU AEROSOL INTRODUCTION PATH">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">OUTSIDE-TO-ICU AEROSOL INTRODUCTION PATH</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure limits outward leakage but also establishes an inward pressure-driven pathway by which outside aerosol can be introduced into the ICU.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.79</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">62e55c5d-3b2a-4772-a671-df2065fce8b1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="COUGH-GENERATED DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-GENERATED DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">The negative-pressure downwards-blowing fan case partially limits droplet spread by driving most droplets downward to the bottom surface or into evaporation, but containment is incomplete because a few droplets recirculate and travel farther.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.66</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_36</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="CIRCULAR HOLE">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">CIRCULAR HOLE</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">The negative-pressure boundary condition is applied at the circular hole in the downwards-blowing fan approximation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="DROPLETS AND AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">DROPLET AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative pressure supports containment of droplet aerosols generated within the isolation ward by reducing outward airflow from the ward to surrounding spaces.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_51</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE PRESSURE" target="RESPIRATORY AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">RESPIRATORY BIOAEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">In a negative pressure isolation ward, the pressure relationship supports containment of respiratory bioaerosols generated by respiratory behaviors by encouraging inward airflow and reducing outward migration.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
