      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d8">NOVEL CORONAVIRUS-LADEN DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative-pressure isolation is relevant to containment of pathogen-laden respiratory droplets such as novel coronavirus-laden droplets, although the cited coronavirus droplet study is a separate airborne-dispersion reference rather than a direct ward-specific measurement.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.58</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
