    <edge source="NO-VENTILATION CASE" target="COUGH-GENERATED INFECTIOUS DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">NO-VENTILATION CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-GENERATED INFECTIOUS DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The no-ventilation condition was evaluated by examining cough-droplet dispersion and removal performance in the stagnant or weakly mixed lift environment.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.83</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NO-VENTILATION CASE" target="CO2">
      <data key="d7">NO VENTILATION CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">CO2</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The no-ventilation case was assessed using mass CO2 concentration. It was less effective at exhausting CO2 and reached 35 ppm in 15 seconds.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NO-VENTILATION CASE" target="COUGH-RELEASED DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">NO VENTILATION CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-RELEASED DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The no-ventilation case was evaluated by liquid droplet dispersion behavior. In this scenario, droplets fell downward and evaporated before reaching the floor, making it appear safest in terms of droplet dispersion.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NO-VENTILATION CASE" target="COUGH PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">NO VENTILATION CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The no-ventilation case was assessed by the amount of cough particles removed and exhibited removal behavior comparable to the upward-blowing fan case, though slightly less effective for droplet deletion.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UPWARD-EXHAUST FAN CASE" target="CO2 CONCENTRATION">
