      <data key="d8">CO2 CONCENTRATION</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The upward-exhaust fan condition was assessed using CO2 concentration as a tracer-gas metric for ventilation performance.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UPWARD-EXHAUST FAN CASE" target="COUGH-GENERATED INFECTIOUS DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">UPWARD-EXHAUST FAN CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-GENERATED INFECTIOUS DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The upward-exhaust fan condition was evaluated by examining how cough-generated droplets dispersed and were removed from the hospital lift.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE" target="CO2 CONCENTRATION">
      <data key="d7">DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">CO2 CONCENTRATION</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The downward-blowing fan condition was assessed using CO2 concentration to compare contaminant accumulation against the other ventilation strategies. | The downward-blowing fan air-distribution scenario is assessed using CO2 concentration over time to compare its modeled airborne exposure and infection-risk behavior against the other scenarios.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE" target="COUGH-GENERATED INFECTIOUS DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-GENERATED INFECTIOUS DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The downward-blowing fan condition was evaluated by examining droplet dispersion and removal behavior under downward airflow.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE" target="CO2">
      <data key="d7">DOWNWARDS-BLOWING CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">CO2</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The downward-blowing case was assessed by measuring CO2 concentration in ppm and comparing it with the upward-blowing and no-fan cases. | The downwards-blowing fan case was assessed using CO2 concentration dynamics. It showed cyclic and harmonious behavior, and its aspiration-phase CO2 decreases were similar to those of the upward-blowing fan case.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE" target="NO FAN CASE">
      <data key="d7">DOWNWARDS-BLOWING FAN CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">NO FAN CASE</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">Both the downwards-blowing fan and no fan cases are described as cyclic and harmonious, indicating similarly regular CO2 concentration cycles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.66</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE" target="EXHALED CO2">
      <data key="d7">DOWNWARDS-BLOWING FAN CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">EXHALED CO2</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The downwards-blowing airflow pattern was evaluated using CO2-based infection probability. Its values were initially similar to the upwards-blowing case and later converged to a similar final value, about 81.2% in the final second.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE" target="PATHOGEN-BEARING COUGH DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">DOWNWARDS-BLOWING FAN CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">PATHOGEN-BEARING COUGH DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The downwards-blowing airflow pattern was assessed by the droplet quantity fraction and showed the fastest early removal. About 30% of droplets evaporated or were quickly expelled within roughly 1.5 seconds, and removal was noticeable immediately.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE" target="COUGH-GENERATED DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">DOWNWARDS-BLOWING CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-GENERATED DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The downward-blowing airflow pattern was assessed by tracking cough-generated droplet removal, showing the fastest 90% removal time at 3.5 seconds.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE" target="DOMAIN-AVERAGED CONTAMINANT CONCENTRATION">
      <data key="d7">DOWNWARDS-BLOWING FAN CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">DOMAIN-AVERAGED CONTAMINANT CONCENTRATION</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The downward-blowing fan case was assessed using a ppm-based domain-averaged concentration metric, including comparison at the 20.2 ppm convergence point.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.77</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNWARD-BLOWING FAN CASE" target="PATHOGEN-LADEN EXPIRATORY DROPLETS">
