      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Higher occupancy can increase the amount of exhaled respiratory aerosol introduced into indoor air, thereby increasing the significance of aerosol dispersion patterns for exposure monitoring.</data>
