    <edge source="UPWARDS-BLOWING CASE" target="CO2">
      <data key="d7">UPWARDS-BLOWING CASE</data>
      <data key="d8">CO2</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The upward-blowing case was assessed by measuring CO2 concentration in ppm; it was generally below the no-fan concentration but briefly exceeded it during the first second. | The upward-blowing fan case was evaluated through CO2 concentration and transport behavior, including the establishment of a CO2 exhausting stream and the observation of irregular, non-homogeneous cycles. | The upwards-blowing fan case was evaluated using CO2 concentration results, but its renewed air did not quickly affect gas emissions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_29</data>
