      <data key="d8">EXHALED CO2</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The upwards-blowing airflow pattern was evaluated using CO2-based infection probability, with exhaled CO2 acting as the tracer. Its probability values were similar to the downwards-blowing case until about the 7th second, then rose slightly more, reaching about a 12% difference until around the 12.5th second before converging to about 80.6% in the final second.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
