      <data key="d8">PATHOGEN-BEARING COUGH DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The upwards-blowing airflow pattern was assessed by the fraction of cough droplets missing from the domain. Droplets appeared around the 5th second; removal began about 1 second after coughing and required about 2 seconds to eliminate roughly 10% of droplets, indicating slower removal than the downwards-blowing case.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b</data>
    </edge>
