      <data key="d8">EXHALED CO2</data>
      <data key="d9">PATTERN_MEASURED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The no-fan airflow pattern was included in the CO2-based infection probability comparison shown in Figure 8. Across all three scenarios, increased infection risk was attributed primarily to higher exhaled CO2 amounts rather than to exposure time alone.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.74</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">c3ec75c5-6024-45ba-a0b0-8dd0c746991b_chunk_32</data>
