      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">High-emitting infectious individuals can increase aerosolized SARS-CoV-2 transmission risk, and the text notes that CO2 approaches generally cannot account for this variation in individual infectivity. | High emitters increase the potential airborne SARS-CoV-2 burden because their high viral loads and respiratory particle emissions can produce substantially greater infectious aerosol release.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
