      <data key="d8">PRONOUNCED AEROSOL PLUME BEHIND THE EMITTER</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">NVV with an ascending spectator area produced a pronounced aerosol plume behind the emitter, especially for emitter position A14.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NVV WITH AN ASCENDING SPECTATOR AREA" target="CONTAMINATION OF THE ENTIRE VENUE">
      <data key="d7">NVV WITH AN ASCENDING SPECTATOR AREA</data>
      <data key="d8">CONTAMINATION OF THE ENTIRE VENUE</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">Unlike DVV, NVV caused aerosol particles to contaminate the entire venue, expanding exposure beyond the seats directly behind the emitter.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NVV WITH AN ASCENDING SPECTATOR AREA" target="COVID-19 AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION">
      <data key="d7">NVV WITH AN ASCENDING SPECTATOR AREA</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19 AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">NVV was associated with the highest numerically derived global COVID-19 airborne transmission risk, with R_CFD about 2 to 2.6 secondary cases.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
