      <data key="d7">PREFERENTIAL BACKWARD AEROSOL FLOW</data>
      <data key="d8">AROUND THE EMITTER</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The MVV-associated aerosol pathway was linked to the region around the emitter, where increased CFD-derived exposure probability values occurred in all directions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PREFERENTIAL BACKWARD AEROSOL FLOW" target="UPPER RIGHT CORNER">
      <data key="d7">PREFERENTIAL BACKWARD AEROSOL FLOW</data>
      <data key="d8">UPPER RIGHT CORNER</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The backward aerosol flow under MVV preferentially transported particles toward the upper right corner of the venue.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTAMINATION OF THE ENTIRE VENUE" target="ENTIRE VENUE">
      <data key="d7">CONTAMINATION OF THE ENTIRE VENUE</data>
      <data key="d8">ENTIRE VENUE</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The NVV contamination pattern extended throughout the entire indoor venue.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTAMINATION OF THE ENTIRE VENUE" target="5 TO 10 SPECTATORS EXCEEDING R_ACC UNDER MVV">
      <data key="d7">CONTAMINATION OF THE ENTIRE VENUE</data>
      <data key="d8">22 TO 170 SPECTATORS EXCEEDING R_ACC UNDER NVV</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The broad venue-wide contamination under NVV corresponded to 22 to 170 spectators, or 9–70% of the audience, exceeding the accumulated risk threshold.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HIGH EMITTER 90TH PERCENTILE" target="COVID-19 AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION">
      <data key="d7">HIGH EMITTER 90TH PERCENTILE</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19 AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The high-emitter condition represents an occupant source scenario with elevated aerosol emission potential and therefore relevance to increased airborne COVID-19 transmission risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSIVE EMITTER" target="HIGH EMITTER 90TH PERCENTILE">
      <data key="d7">PASSIVE EMITTER</data>
      <data key="d8">HIGH EMITTER 90TH PERCENTILE</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The high-emitter scenario was compared with the passive-emitter condition; the text notes that aerosol distribution for the high emitter was similar in pattern and remained dependent on emitter position and ventilation strategy.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSIVE EMITTER" target="AEROSOLIZED PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">PASSIVE EMITTER</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOL PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The passive emitter served as a lower-emission comparison source for aerosol-particle distribution. The high-emitter scenario followed a similar spatial dependence on emitter position but with greater risk due to enhanced release.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.65</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSIVE EMITTER" target="AIRBORNE PATH FROM STALLS TO BALCONIES">
      <data key="d7">PASSIVE EMITTER</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE PATH FROM STALLS TO BALCONIES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The passive emitter acted as the aerosol source that increased contaminant transport along the path from stalls to balconies.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENUES" target="DISPLACEMENT VENTILATION">
      <data key="d7">VENUES</data>
      <data key="d8">DISPLACEMENT VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The venues were evaluated using displacement ventilation. Under this pattern, the high-emitter scenario produced a wider and more pronounced increased-risk zone, particularly for emitter positions E6 and B9.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENUES" target="MIXING VENTILATION">
      <data key="d7">VENUES</data>
      <data key="d8">MIXING VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The venues were evaluated using mixing ventilation. In the high-emitter case, this air-distribution pattern was associated with aerosol spread throughout the venue and elevated individual infection risk at nearly all positions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENUES" target="NATURAL VENTILATION">
      <data key="d7">VENUES</data>
      <data key="d8">NATURAL VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The venues were evaluated using natural ventilation. In the high-emitter case, this pattern was associated with broad aerosol distribution and increased modeled individual infection risk across nearly all spectator positions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HIGH EMITTING INDIVIDUAL" target="INFECTIOUS AEROSOL">
      <data key="d7">HIGH EMITTING INDIVIDUAL</data>
      <data key="d8">INFECTIOUS AEROSOL</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The high-emitting individual released enhanced quantities of infectious aerosol, increasing modeled individual and global infection risk across the studied venues.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.96</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HIGH EMITTING INDIVIDUAL" target="AEROSOLIZED PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">HIGH EMITTING INDIVIDUAL</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOL PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The high-emitter condition increased aerosol-particle release compared with a passive-emitter condition. The resulting particle distribution depended on source position and ventilation strategy.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
