      <data key="d10">A high-emitting actor increases airborne exposure risk for the ensemble, particularly if the stage is not effectively served by ventilation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HIGH EMITTING SPECTATOR AT B9" target="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19 INFECTIOUS AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">HIGH EMITTING SPECTATOR AT B9</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19 INFECTIOUS AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">A high-emitting spectator at B9 substantially increased airborne infection risk under 50% reduced airflow, with almost all spectators exceeding the accumulated risk threshold and 8.36 predicted new COVID-19 cases.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SILENT PASSIVE EMITTER" target="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19 INFECTIOUS AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">SILENT PASSIVE EMITTER</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19 INFECTIOUS AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Even the lower-emission silent passive emitter contributed to COVID-19 risk under reduced airflow, with secondary infections increasing 2.3-fold to 0.61 and more spectators exceeding the accumulated risk threshold.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SILENT PASSIVE EMITTER" target="AIRBORNE INFECTIOUS AEROSOL">
      <data key="d7">SILENT PASSIVE EMITTER</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE INFECTIOUS AEROSOL</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The silent passive emitter contributes a low level of infectious aerosol to the venue and defines the lower-emission source condition.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SILENT PASSIVE EMITTER" target="SARS-COV-2 WILD-TYPE">
      <data key="d7">SILENT, PASSIVE EMITTER</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 WILD-TYPE</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">A silent, passive infectious emitter can release SARS-CoV-2 wild-type aerosols, but the text characterizes this background-actor scenario as only low risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.39</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SILENT PASSIVE EMITTER" target="OMICRON VARIANT">
      <data key="d7">SILENT, PASSIVE EMITTER</data>
      <data key="d8">OMICRON VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">A silent, passive infectious emitter can release Omicron-containing aerosols, but the text indicates that this scenario poses relatively low airborne transmission risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.41</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
