      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">A fully occupied audience increases the number of people potentially exposed to airborne SARS-CoV-2 when an infectious emitter is present. This relationship reflects increased exposure opportunity rather than each audience member necessarily being infectious.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.68</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_48</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SEDENTARY PASSIVE EMITTER WITH AVERAGE VIRAL LOAD" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">SEDENTARY PASSIVE EMITTER WITH AVERAGE VIRAL LOAD</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The sedentary passive infectious emitter emits SARS-CoV-2-containing respiratory aerosols or quanta at an average viral-load level, contributing to airborne exposure and subsequent infection-risk calculations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SLIGHTLY ACTIVE EMITTER WITH 90TH-PERCENTILE HIGH VIRAL LOAD" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">SLIGHTLY ACTIVE EMITTER WITH 90TH-PERCENTILE HIGH VIRAL LOAD</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The slightly active infectious emitter with 90th-percentile viral load represents a higher-emission scenario that increases SARS-CoV-2 aerosol or quanta output relative to the average-load sedentary case.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d14">2c371b3c-bdf6-4d57-aab2-55e74c106206</data>
    </edge>
