      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The effective air exchange rate λEz affects the modeled concentration or exposure to virus-containing particles by increasing dilution and removal through ventilation. Because decay and deposition are neglected in the worst-case scenario, this effective ventilation term is the main removal mechanism represented.</data>
