      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">HEAT-INDUCED AIRFLOW FROM UV-C LUMINAIRES</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room may also contain heat-induced airflow effects from UV-C luminaire heat generation, which are treated as uncertain contributors to the simulation results.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">19fa3b4e-2c3d-44b1-ae20-59902abc601a_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">19fa3b4e-2c3d-44b1-ae20-59902abc601a</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="AIR MIXING IN THE ROOM">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">AIR MIXING IN THE ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room has an air distribution pattern described as strong forced-air mixing dominated by fan- and ventilation-induced flows.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">19fa3b4e-2c3d-44b1-ae20-59902abc601a_chunk_34</data>
      <data key="d14">19fa3b4e-2c3d-44b1-ae20-59902abc601a</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="COUGH JET">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH JET</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room contained a cough-jet airflow pattern that spread particles throughout the space and altered local plume dynamics around the occupant.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="LOW-VELOCITY SPEAKING EXHALATION">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">LOW-VELOCITY SPEAKING EXHALATION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room also included the lower-velocity exhalation condition associated with speaking, which was contrasted with coughing and was not observed to slow the human-body buoyant plume.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.73</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="UPWARD BUOYANT PLUME GENERATED BY THE HUMAN BODY">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">UPWARD BUOYANT PLUME GENERATED BY THE HUMAN BODY</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room contained an upward buoyant plume generated by the human body. This occupant-driven thermal airflow pattern interacted differently with coughing and speaking exhalations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="3 ACH">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">36 ACH</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The room has a reported air exchange rate of 36 ACH based on supply airflow and room volume.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.98</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="49 ± 20 ACHT">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">49 ± 20 ACHT</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The room has a measured tracer-derived average air exchange rate of 49 ± 20 ACHT across six measured positions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.96</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="14,800 EACH">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">14,800 EACH</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The room is assigned a calculated equivalent ACH of 14,800 from far-UVC lamp performance, although the text cautions that the calculation depends on a well-mixed assumption that may not apply. | When the poorly mixed room is evaluated using a mixing factor of 10, the estimated equivalent ACH is 1480 with a 95% confidence interval of 200–3600. | The room/far-UVC installation was associated with an unadjusted calculated eACH of 14,800 with 95% CI: 2000–36,000, but this estimate assumes perfect mixing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="POOR MIXING">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">POOR MIXING</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room has poor mixing due to its supply and exhaust configuration. | The room has poor mixing due to the ventilation layout, including nearby ceiling supply and exhaust and a large directional ceiling-to-side airflow. | The room has poor mixing across much of its volume due to airflow short-circuiting and a large ceiling-to-side airflow.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.97</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="SHORT CIRCUITING OF FLOW">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">SHORT CIRCUITING OF FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room has short-circuiting airflow, with supplied air expected to move preferentially toward the door exhaust rather than mix uniformly. | The room exhibits short-circuiting because of the close supply-exhaust layout in the ceiling. This pattern causes air to bypass broader room mixing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="DEAD SPACES">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">DEAD SPACES</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room is expected to contain dead spaces because its airflow layout promotes non-uniform ventilation. | The room contains dead spaces formed by the ventilation layout and nonuniform airflow. These indicate regions of weak air exchange.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="WELL-MIXED SINGLE-COMPARTMENT ASSUMPTION">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">WELL-MIXED SINGLE-COMPARTMENT ASSUMPTION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The initial equivalent ACH calculation assumes a perfectly well-mixed single-compartment room, but the text states this is not appropriate for the actual room.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.74</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="POORLY MIXED AIR DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">POORLY MIXED AIR DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room is evaluated as poorly mixed, meaning its air distribution is nonideal and requires a mixing-factor correction when computing effective ACH and equivalent ACH.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="36 EFFECTIVE ACH">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">36 EFFECTIVE ACH</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">Before the poor-mixing correction is applied, the room is associated with an effective ACH value of 36. | For the poorly mixed room, applying a mixing factor of 10 reduces the effective ACH from 36 to 3.6.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="7.2 EFFECTIVE ACH">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">7.2 EFFECTIVE ACH</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">For the poorly mixed room, applying a mixing factor of 5 reduces the effective ACH from 36 to 7.2.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="2960 EACH">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">2960 EACH</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">When the poorly mixed room is evaluated using a mixing factor of 5, the estimated equivalent ACH is 2960 with a 95% confidence interval of 400–7200.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="IRREGULAR AIRFLOW PATTERNS">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">IRREGULAR AIRFLOW PATTERNS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room has irregular airflow patterns that make extrapolation of aerosolized MNV susceptibility uncertain by affecting residence time and delivered far-UVC dose.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="K-ADJUSTED EACH WITH MIXING FACTOR 5 OR 10">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">K-ADJUSTED EACH WITH MIXING FACTOR 5 OR 10</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The room has a more applicable K-adjusted eACH estimate when a mixing factor of 5 or 10 is incorporated to account for poor mixing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.91</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="ROOM VOLUME">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">ROOM VOLUME</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The room contains the room volume over which ventilation and mixing effectiveness are evaluated.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ROOM" target="IMPERFECT MIXING">
      <data key="d7">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">IMPERFECT MIXING</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The real-world room environment is characterized by imperfect mixing, which motivates use of K mixing factors when estimating effective ACH from far-UVC exposure.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
