    <edge source="FANS" target="ROOM">
      <data key="d7">FANS</data>
      <data key="d8">ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The fans serve the room by producing airflow that affects mixing and airborne particle decay. The text states that fan volume flux influences the surviving fraction and that fan-induced flows dominate room mixing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">19fa3b4e-2c3d-44b1-ae20-59902abc601a_chunk_34</data>
      <data key="d14">19fa3b4e-2c3d-44b1-ae20-59902abc601a</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FANS" target="FORCED AIR FLOWS FROM FANS AND MECHANICAL VENTILATION">
      <data key="d7">FANS</data>
      <data key="d8">FORCED AIR FLOWS FROM FANS AND MECHANICAL VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The fans connect to and generate part of the forced airflow path. Changes in fan volume flux alter the strength of this airflow and consequently the decay behavior of airborne particles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">19fa3b4e-2c3d-44b1-ae20-59902abc601a_chunk_34</data>
      <data key="d14">19fa3b4e-2c3d-44b1-ae20-59902abc601a</data>
    </edge>
