      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE BACTERIAL SPORES</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The 0 ACH condition affects airborne bacterial spore survival measurements by removing ventilation-based dilution from the scenario, so changes in surviving fraction reflect natural decay and UV-related inactivation processes. | The 0 ACH condition provides a no-air-change baseline for evaluating airborne bacterial spore decay.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">19fa3b4e-2c3d-44b1-ae20-59902abc601a_chunk_36</data>
