      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The 0 ACH condition affects airborne mycobacteria survival measurements by eliminating air-change-driven removal, making measured decay depend primarily on natural biological decay and UV-related inactivation. | The 0 ACH condition provides a no-air-change baseline for evaluating airborne mycobacteria decay.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
