      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The possibly infected mask wearer can emit airborne viruses through breathing, coughing, or sneezing. The text emphasizes that masks reduce dispersion of larger respiratory drops but are less effective for fine aerosols below 5 µm.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.83</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
