      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Infected people shed respiratory viruses in exhaled breath, increasing airborne viral presence and potential transmission. The cited studies concern transmission of airborne viruses by infected people and the mitigating effect of face masks.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.89</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_14</data>
