    <edge source="HUMAN PRESENCE AND RESPIRATORY ACTIVITY" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">HUMAN PRESENCE AND RESPIRATORY ACTIVITY</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Respiratory activities by occupants, such as coughing, sneezing, and conversation, can increase the release of particles potentially carrying SARS-CoV-2 into the air.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.74</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HUMAN PRESENCE AND RESPIRATORY ACTIVITY" target="RESPIRATORY PARTICLE AIR PATH">
      <data key="d7">HUMAN PRESENCE AND RESPIRATORY ACTIVITY</data>
      <data key="d8">RESPIRATORY PARTICLE AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Human presence can increase the complexity of respiratory-particle air paths by influencing local airflow and dispersion, although this factor was ignored in the cited simplified simulations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.62</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM" target="RECIRCULATING INDOOR AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d7">SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">RECIRCULATING INDOOR AIRFLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The office-type room has a recirculating indoor airflow pattern when served by an air-conditioning unit that recirculates the same air, increasing the potential for particle redistribution.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM" target="BENEFICIAL OR HARMFUL AIRFLOW PATTERNS">
      <data key="d7">SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">BENEFICIAL OR HARMFUL AIRFLOW PATTERNS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room can exhibit beneficial or harmful airflow patterns depending on the positioning of air-conditioning systems, open windows, and doors.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING UNIT RECIRCULATING ROOM AIR" target="SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM">
      <data key="d7">AIR-CONDITIONING UNIT RECIRCULATING ROOM AIR</data>
      <data key="d8">SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The air-conditioning unit serves the modeled office-type room by recirculating indoor air. In the cited coughing or sneezing scenario, this service condition can spread infectious particles rather than remove them.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING UNIT RECIRCULATING ROOM AIR" target="RECIRCULATING INDOOR AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d7">AIR-CONDITIONING UNIT RECIRCULATING ROOM AIR</data>
      <data key="d8">RECIRCULATING INDOOR AIRFLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The recirculating air-conditioning unit generates a recirculating airflow distribution pattern inside the room.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM">
      <data key="d7">AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The air-conditioning systems serve the occupied office-type room and shape its internal airflow. Their placement was evaluated as a determinant of beneficial or harmful airborne-particle transport.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS">
      <data key="d7">AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The air-conditioning systems serve the occupied room by conditioning and moving air. Their placement is important because it can shape whether airflow carries virion-laden particles away from or toward receptors.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="BENEFICIAL OR HARMFUL AIRFLOW PATTERNS">
      <data key="d7">AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">BENEFICIAL OR HARMFUL AIRFLOW PATTERNS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The position of air-conditioning systems helps produce specific air-distribution patterns in the room. Depending on the resulting flow, the pattern can suppress or enhance dissemination of virion-laden particles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="RESTAURANT DINING ROOM">
      <data key="d7">AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d8">RESTAURANT DINING ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The air-conditioning system serves the restaurant dining room by supplying air and shaping the ventilation conditions under which aerosol dispersion was simulated.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="RAILWAY COACHES">
      <data key="d7">AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">RAILWAY COACHES</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">Air-conditioning systems serve railway coaches as part of the range of ventilation methods used in rail vehicles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.77</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_84</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="CFD-MODELED AIRFLOW AND AERODYNAMICS">
      <data key="d7">AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">CFD-MODELED AIRFLOW AND AERODYNAMICS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The referenced CFD analysis of COVID-19 spread with air conditioning systems implies that HVAC operation produces airflow patterns relevant to droplet and aerosol transport.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.65</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_121</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="SUBWAY CABINS">
      <data key="d7">AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">SUBWAY CABINS</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The air-conditioning systems serve the subway cabin environment by providing ventilation and airflow needed for normal cabin air handling.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="MIXING CHAMBER">
      <data key="d7">AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">MIXING CHAMBER</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The air-conditioning system connects to the mixing chamber where return air and fresh air pass through the purification pathway.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="CP GENERATOR">
      <data key="d7">AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">CP GENERATOR</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The CP generator initially relies on the driving force provided by the air-conditioning system, making the two functionally connected.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING SYSTEMS" target="AIR DUCT STRUCTURE">
      <data key="d7">AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">AIR DUCT STRUCTURE</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The air-conditioning system connects to the air duct structure that organizes airflow for distributing air and purifying materials.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EXTRACTION AND AIR FILTRATION OR GERMICIDAL AIR-TREATMENT SYSTEMS" target="SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM">
      <data key="d7">EXTRACTION AND AIR FILTRATION OR GERMICIDAL AIR-TREATMENT SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">SINGLE UNFURNISHED AND VENTILATED OFFICE-REPRESENTATIVE ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">Extraction, filtration, and germicidal air-treatment systems are recommended as components of ventilation serving the room to reduce the risk of a virion-laden indoor environment.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SINGLE PERSON COUGHING OR SNEEZING" target="INFECTIOUS AGENT CARRIED BY DROPS AND DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">SINGLE PERSON COUGHING OR SNEEZING</data>
      <data key="d8">INFECTIOUS AGENT CARRIED BY DROPS AND DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">A coughing or sneezing person increases the release of respiratory drops, droplets, and particles that may carry an infectious agent into the room air.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SINGLE PERSON COUGHING OR SNEEZING" target="CORONAVIRUS">
      <data key="d7">SINGLE PERSON COUGHING OR SNEEZING</data>
      <data key="d8">CORONAVIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">If the coughing or sneezing person is infectious, this occupancy condition increases the potential airborne coronavirus burden through emitted respiratory particles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS" target="INFECTIOUS AGENT CARRIED BY DROPS AND DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">INFECTIOUS AGENT CARRIED BY DROPS AND DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence of one or two occupants increases the possible source and exposure conditions for infectious particles when an occupant emits pathogen-bearing droplets.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.65</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS" target="VIRION-LADEN PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRION-LADEN PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Occupants can act as respiratory emission sources if infected. The one- or two-occupant condition therefore determines the potential introduction and exposure geometry of virion-laden particles in the room.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.68</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UNMASKED HUMANOID MANIKINS" target="INFECTIOUS AGENT CARRIED BY DROPS AND DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">UNMASKED HUMANOID MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d8">INFECTIOUS AGENT CARRIED BY DROPS AND DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The unmasked simulated manikins represent occupants without mask-based source control, so emitted respiratory particles are not blocked by face coverings in the modeled scenarios.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.68</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS" target="BENEFICIAL OR HARMFUL AIRFLOW PATTERNS">
      <data key="d7">E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">BENEFICIAL OR HARMFUL AIRFLOW PATTERNS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The modeled occupied room can exhibit airflow patterns that are beneficial or harmful for infection control. These patterns are influenced by HVAC placement and by the location of open windows and doors.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS" target="CEILING-TO-SIDE WALL VENTILATION DESIGN">
      <data key="d7">E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">CEILING-TO-SIDE WALL VENTILATION DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room may be configured with a ceiling-to-side wall ventilation pattern. The cited simulations indicate that this layout may be preferable for particle management in both standing and sitting positions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.83</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS" target="CEILING-TO-CEILING CONFIGURATION">
      <data key="d7">E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">CEILING-TO-CEILING CONFIGURATION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room may also use a ceiling-to-ceiling ventilation configuration. This layout is compared with ceiling-to-side wall ventilation and is described as less favorable in the cited results.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS" target="HIGHER VENTILATION RATE">
      <data key="d7">E-TYPE ROOM OCCUPIED BY ONE OR TWO OCCUPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">HIGHER VENTILATION RATE</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The occupied room is evaluated under a higher ventilation-rate condition. No numerical air-change rate is provided, but the condition functions as an ACH-related control variable.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HIGHER VENTILATION RATE" target="VIRION-LADEN PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">HIGHER VENTILATION RATE</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRION-LADEN PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">A higher ventilation rate affects dilution and removal of virion-laden particles, but the text states that it does not guarantee better removal. Effectiveness depends on the airflow pattern and whether particles are transported to exhaust paths or to receptor locations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HIGHER VENTILATION RATE" target="RESPIRATORY DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">HIGHER VENTILATION RATE</data>
      <data key="d8">RESPIRATORY DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation rate affects the residence time and removal of respiratory droplets. However, under certain airflow patterns, droplets can still reach receptor points and persist for durations up to 30 minutes.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HIGHER VENTILATION RATE" target="COVID-19 VECTORS">
      <data key="d7">HIGHER VENTILATION RATE</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19 VECTORS</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Higher ventilation can influence the dilution and transport of COVID-19-related airborne vectors, but the text cautions that increased rate alone is insufficient if the distribution pattern allows exposure or persistence.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VIRION-LADEN PARTICLES" target="DISSEMINATION OF VIRION-LADEN PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">VIRION-LADEN PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d8">DISSEMINATION OF VIRION-LADEN PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">Virion-laden particles have a simulated distribution pattern within the coach, represented by their spatial movement, concentration, and transmission through the ventilated occupied space.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TWO HUMANOID MANIKINS SEATED OR STANDING FACE TO FACE" target="COVID-19 VECTORS">
      <data key="d7">TWO HUMANOID MANIKINS SEATED OR STANDING FACE TO FACE</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19 VECTORS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The face-to-face manikin arrangement models source-to-receptor exposure to COVID-19 vectors emitted during respiratory mechanisms. Seated and standing positions are both considered.</data>
