      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OPEN DOOR OF THE CLASSROOM" target="CLASSROOM">
      <data key="d7">OPEN DOOR OF THE CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The open door connects the classroom to the outlet path, allowing air and suspended particles to exit the modeled space.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TEACHER WHO COUGHED IN FRONT OF A CLASS" target="COUGH-GENERATED PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">TEACHER WHO COUGHED IN FRONT OF A CLASS</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-GENERATED PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The coughing teacher is the infectious occupancy source that increases the release of cough-generated particles into the classroom air.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TEACHER WHO COUGHED IN FRONT OF A CLASS" target="COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">TEACHER WHO COUGHED IN FRONT OF A CLASS</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The infected teacher represents the occupancy source for potential Covid-19 airborne spread in the classroom scenario.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CLASSROOM OCCUPANTS AND SEATED STUDENTS" target="COUGH-GENERATED PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">CLASSROOM OCCUPANTS AND SEATED STUDENTS</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-GENERATED PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence, shape, and placement of classroom occupants influence the modeled particle field because individuals act as obstacles affecting dispersion around seats, especially near the infected teacher.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS" target="UPWARD CUBICLE PARTICLE REMOVAL PATTERN">
      <data key="d7">TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS</data>
      <data key="d8">UPWARD CUBICLE PARTICLE REMOVAL PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The transparent cabins promote upward removal of particle-laden air, especially when aided by fan suction, ceiling exit holes, or filters.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS" target="SURROUNDING CLASSROOM OCCUPIED AREA">
      <data key="d7">TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS</data>
      <data key="d8">SURROUNDING CLASSROOM OCCUPIED AREA</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The transparent cabins are located within and adjacent to the surrounding occupied classroom area, creating a boundary where filtered or unfiltered air may pass toward other occupants.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR-CONDITIONING CONFIGURATION" target="CLASSROOM">
      <data key="d7">AIR-CONDITIONING CONFIGURATION</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The air-conditioning configuration serves the classroom by supplying fresh air and removing stale air carrying virion-loaded particles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HEPA FILTER ATOP CUBICLES" target="TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS">
      <data key="d7">HEPA FILTER ATOP CUBICLES</data>
      <data key="d8">TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The HEPA filter serves the transparent cabins by filtering particle-laden air leaving the cabin region before it reaches the rest of the classroom.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HEPA FILTER ATOP CUBICLES" target="SURROUNDING CLASSROOM OCCUPIED AREA">
      <data key="d7">HEPA FILTER ATOP CUBICLES</data>
      <data key="d8">SURROUNDING CLASSROOM OCCUPIED AREA</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">By filtering air leaving the cubicles, the HEPA filter indirectly serves the surrounding classroom occupied area with cleaner air.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CUBICLE EXHAUST FAN" target="TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS">
      <data key="d7">CUBICLE EXHAUST FAN</data>
      <data key="d8">TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The fan serves the cabin airflow system by sucking air carrying particles upward and out of the cabin region; faster suction reduces the number of particles left in the classroom.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CUBICLE EXHAUST FAN" target="CLASSROOM">
      <data key="d7">CUBICLE EXHAUST FAN</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The cubicle exhaust fan indirectly serves the classroom by accelerating removal of particle-laden air, reducing particle accumulation in the room.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LARGE AIR PURIFIERS" target="CLASSROOMS WITHOUT PRE-INSTALLED VENTILATION">
      <data key="d7">LARGE AIR PURIFIERS</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOMS WITHOUT PRE-INSTALLED VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">Large air purifiers are considered supplemental air-cleaning interventions for classrooms that often lack built-in ventilation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.67</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LARGE AIR PURIFIERS" target="CLASSROOM">
      <data key="d7">LARGE AIR PURIFIERS</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">Large air purifiers are evaluated as supplemental air-cleaning equipment operating within classrooms.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_124</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SIDE-WALL FRESH AIR SUPPLY AT 1 M HEIGHT" target="AIR-CONDITIONING CONFIGURATION">
      <data key="d7">SIDE-WALL FRESH AIR SUPPLY AT 1 M HEIGHT</data>
      <data key="d8">AIR-CONDITIONING CONFIGURATION</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The side-wall fresh air supply path is part of the optimized air-conditioning configuration.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.83</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SIDE-WALL FRESH AIR SUPPLY AT 1 M HEIGHT" target="CLASSROOM">
      <data key="d7">SIDE-WALL FRESH AIR SUPPLY AT 1 M HEIGHT</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Fresh air enters the classroom through side-wall openings located approximately one meter above the floor.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CEILING STALE AIR EXHAUST" target="CLASSROOM">
      <data key="d7">CEILING STALE AIR EXHAUST</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The ceiling exhaust path connects the classroom air volume to an upward removal route for stale, particle-laden air.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CEILING EXIT HOLES" target="CEILING STALE AIR EXHAUST">
      <data key="d7">CEILING EXIT HOLES</data>
      <data key="d8">CEILING STALE AIR EXHAUST</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Ceiling exit holes function as openings in the ceiling exhaust pathway through which particles are directed upward and out.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OPEN-ROOF CUBICLE AIR PATH" target="TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS">
      <data key="d7">OPEN-ROOF CUBICLE AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">TRANSPARENT CABINS AROUND STUDENTS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The open-roof cubicle air path connects the cabin interior to upward airflow routes, enabling particles to rise toward exhaust or filtration.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OPEN-ROOF CUBICLE AIR PATH" target="CEILING EXIT HOLES">
      <data key="d7">OPEN-ROOF CUBICLE AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">CEILING EXIT HOLES</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The open-roof cabin pathway supports upward movement of contaminated air toward ceiling exit holes.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.68</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HOURLY AIR EXCHANGE VOLUME IN THE CLASSROOM" target="VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">HOURLY AIR EXCHANGE VOLUME IN THE CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The number of particles in airflow was inversely correlated with hourly air exchange volume, meaning higher exchange volume reduced airborne virion-loaded particle burden.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SIDE-WALL SUPPLY AND CEILING-EXHAUST VENTILATION PATTERN" target="VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">SIDE-WALL SUPPLY AND CEILING-EXHAUST VENTILATION PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The optimized supply-and-exhaust airflow pattern affects virion-loaded particle distribution by moving contaminated air upward to ceiling exhaust rather than allowing broader room dispersion.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UPWARD CUBICLE PARTICLE REMOVAL PATTERN" target="VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">UPWARD CUBICLE PARTICLE REMOVAL PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The upward cubicle removal pattern lowers particle residence in the classroom by directing virion-loaded particles up and out or through filtration.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INFECTED STUDENT BREATHING OR SNEEZING" target="VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">INFECTED STUDENT BREATHING OR SNEEZING</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">An infected student breathing or sneezing emits virion-loaded respiratory particles into the classroom airflow.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MANY STUDENTS BREATHING AND TEACHER SPEAKING LOUDLY" target="VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">MANY STUDENTS BREATHING AND TEACHER SPEAKING LOUDLY</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRION-LOADED RESPIRATORY PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Many breathing students and a loudly speaking teacher increase respiratory aerosol generation and may increase airborne virion-loaded particle burden when infectious occupants are present.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR PURIFIER INSTALLED IN THE CLASSROOM" target="CLASSROOM">
      <data key="d7">AIR PURIFIER INSTALLED IN THE CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The air purifier serves the classroom by locally cleaning recirculated room air. Its placement, flow rate, and efficiency influence the simulated spread of virulent particles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.91</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR PURIFIER INSTALLED IN THE CLASSROOM" target="AIR PURIFIER VOLUMETRIC FLOW RATE">
      <data key="d7">AIR PURIFIER INSTALLED IN THE CLASSROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">AIR PURIFIER VOLUMETRIC FLOW RATE</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The air purifier is characterized by a volumetric flow rate, treated here as an ACH-like air-cleaning rate parameter because it controls how much air is processed.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.83</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR PURIFIER VOLUMETRIC FLOW RATE" target="CLASSROOM PARTICLE TRANSPORT AND DISPERSION">
      <data key="d7">AIR PURIFIER VOLUMETRIC FLOW RATE</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOM PARTICLE TRANSPORT AND DISPERSION</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The purifier flow rate affects the classroom particle distribution by altering how rapidly pathogen-laden air is removed or redirected.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FULL CLASS CAPACITY" target="VIRULENT PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">FULL CLASS CAPACITY</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRULENT PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Full classroom capacity represents a higher occupant load with more potential receptors and greater opportunities for exposure to virulent particles, although mask wearing made modeled infection risk comparable to half-capacity operation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.73</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="STUDENT ASSUMED TO BE INFECTED" target="VIRULENT PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">STUDENT ASSUMED TO BE INFECTED</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRULENT PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The infected student increases the airborne pathogen burden by serving as the emission source for virulent particles in the classroom scenario.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PERSON SITTING NEXT TO THE STUDENT ASSUMED TO BE INFECTED" target="STUDENT ASSUMED TO BE INFECTED">
      <data key="d7">PERSON SITTING NEXT TO THE STUDENT ASSUMED TO BE INFECTED</data>
      <data key="d8">STUDENT ASSUMED TO BE INFECTED</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The receptor occupant is seated next to the infected student. This adjacency explains why air-purifier location had less influence on that person’s exposure than on more distant occupants.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VIRULENT PARTICLES" target="CLASSROOM PARTICLE TRANSPORT AND DISPERSION">
      <data key="d7">VIRULENT PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d8">CLASSROOM PARTICLE TRANSPORT AND DISPERSION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The virulent particles are represented through the modeled classroom transport and dispersion pattern, which determines where infectious aerosol exposure occurs.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="RESTAURANT IN GUANGZHOU" target="RESTAURANT SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL PATHOGEN DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">RESTAURANT IN GUANGZHOU</data>
