      <data key="d8">BUOYANT PLUME ABOVE THE MANIKIN'S HEAD</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The manikin's body heat generates and strengthens the upward buoyant plume above its head.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BREATHING MANIKIN" target="FREE CONVECTION FROM OCCUPANT HEAT SOURCES">
      <data key="d7">BREATHING MANIKIN</data>
      <data key="d8">FREE CONVECTION FROM OCCUPANT HEAT SOURCES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The breathing manikin represents an occupant breathing source that contributes warm exhaled air and therefore supports thermal-convection effects in the local simulation region.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.64</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_83</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NO-MASK BREATHING CONDITION" target="MICROMETRIC DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">NO-MASK BREATHING CONDITION</data>
      <data key="d8">MICROMETRIC DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">In the no-mask condition, the manikin's breathing releases micrometric droplets directly into the surrounding air without mask interception.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
