      <data key="d10">Compartment #1 participates in the end-to-middle airflow pattern, with air moving from this end of the coach toward the middle. | Compartment #2 is the central receiving and extraction region of the end-to-middle airflow pattern. | Compartment #3 participates in the end-to-middle airflow pattern, with air moving from this end of the coach toward the middle.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_90</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="92% SEATED-PASSENGER OCCUPANCY IN COMPARTMENT 1" target="PASSENGER-SECRETED DROPS AND DROPLETS DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">92% SEATED-PASSENGER OCCUPANCY IN COMPARTMENT 1</data>
      <data key="d8">PASSENGER-SECRETED DROPS AND DROPLETS DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The 92% seated-passenger occupancy in compartment 1 represents a high local source density for passenger-secreted drops and droplets, affecting their simulated distribution. | The 100% seated-passenger occupancy in compartment 3 represents maximum local seated occupancy, increasing the number of potential respiratory droplet emission sources in that compartment.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_53</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="COACH OCCUPATION RATE" target="PASSENGER-SECRETED DROPS AND DROPLETS DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">COACH OCCUPATION RATE</data>
      <data key="d8">PASSENGER-SECRETED DROPS AND DROPLETS DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The text states that varying the coach occupation rate could be used to examine its influence on the distribution of drops and droplets. Higher occupancy would increase the number and density of passenger emission sources.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_53</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MASKED AND NON-MASKED MANIKINS" target="LOCAL FLOW NEAR MANIKINS AND MASKS">
      <data key="d7">MASKED AND NON-MASKED MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d8">LOCAL FLOW NEAR MANIKINS AND MASKS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence of manikins increases local airflow-resolution requirements and creates localized flow features near bodies and masks; this relationship reflects occupancy-driven local flow complexity rather than a quantified increase in pathogen concentration.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.48</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_54</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ENTIRE SPACE OF THE CARRIAGE" target="8.7 AIR RENEWAL RATE">
      <data key="d7">ENTIRE SPACE OF THE CARRIAGE</data>
      <data key="d8">8.7 AIR RENEWAL RATE</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">Because ventilation involves the entire carriage space, the full internal volume is subject to the stated renewal rate.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FRESH-AIR SUPPLY FROM EACH END OF THE CARRIAGE" target="RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">FRESH-AIR SUPPLY FROM EACH END OF THE CARRIAGE</data>
      <data key="d8">RAIL COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Fresh outside air is supplied into the rail coach from each end of the carriage.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FRESH-AIR SUPPLY FROM EACH END OF THE CARRIAGE" target="VENTILATION SYSTEM">
      <data key="d7">FRESH-AIR SUPPLY FROM EACH END OF THE CARRIAGE</data>
      <data key="d8">VENTILATION SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The fresh-air supply paths are part of the ventilation system that introduces outside air into the coach.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CEILING SLOTS" target="RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">CEILING SLOTS</data>
      <data key="d8">RAIL COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The ceiling slots connect to the coach interior as the outlet or extraction locations toward which air moves.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CEILING SLOTS" target="VENTILATION SYSTEM">
      <data key="d7">CEILING SLOTS</data>
      <data key="d8">VENTILATION SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The ceiling slots are part of the ventilation pathway used to remove or extract air from the coach.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INLET BOUNDARY CONDITIONS" target="FRESH-AIR SUPPLY FROM EACH END OF THE CARRIAGE">
      <data key="d7">INLET BOUNDARY CONDITIONS</data>
      <data key="d8">FRESH-AIR SUPPLY FROM EACH END OF THE CARRIAGE</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The physical fresh-air supply features are translated into inlet boundary conditions for the airflow simulation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INLET BOUNDARY CONDITIONS" target="CEILING SLOTS">
      <data key="d7">OUTLET BOUNDARY CONDITIONS</data>
      <data key="d8">CEILING SLOTS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The physical extraction through ceiling slots is translated into outlet boundary conditions for the airflow simulation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="8.7 AIR RENEWAL RATE" target="SARS-COV-2 VIRUS">
      <data key="d7">8.7 AIR RENEWAL RATE</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The stated air renewal rate would affect dilution and removal of airborne virus-bearing respiratory particles in the broader dispersion context referenced by the study.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.6</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="3D TURBULENT AIRFLOW" target="ENTIRE SPACE OF THE CARRIAGE">
      <data key="d7">3D TURBULENT AIRFLOW</data>
      <data key="d8">ENTIRE SPACE OF THE CARRIAGE</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The simulated turbulent airflow occupies and moves through the entire internal carriage space.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS" target="3D TURBULENT AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">3D TURBULENT AIRFLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Passenger breathing is introduced after the initial ventilation-only airflow simulation and can add respiratory flow disturbances to the modeled airflow.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS" target="SARS-COV-2 VIRUS">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Passenger breathing may introduce respiratory droplets or aerosols relevant to SARS-CoV-2 dispersion, as indicated by the surrounding study context and cited prior work.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.63</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS" target="BUOYANT THERMAL PLUMES ABOVE PASSENGERS">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">BUOYANT THERMAL PLUMES ABOVE PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Passenger occupancy increases buoyant plume formation because warm air generated by seated bodies rises above the passengers.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_59</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS" target="FREE CONVECTION FROM OCCUPANT HEAT SOURCES">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">FREE CONVECTION FROM OCCUPANT HEAT SOURCES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Passenger occupancy increases thermally driven convection because passengers act as heat sources and exhale warm air.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_83</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS" target="PARTICLES EMITTED BY PASSENGERS">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">PARTICLES EMITTED BY PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Passengers are the source of the emitted particles; greater passenger presence would increase the potential particle source load.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_85</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS" target="PASSENGER-EMITTED DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">PASSENGER-EMITTED DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Passengers act as droplet sources; greater or denser occupancy increases the amount and spatial extent of emitted respiratory droplets.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_86</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS" target="PASSENGER-EMITTED SARS-COV-2-LADEN PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">PASSENGER-EMITTED SARS-COV-2-LADEN PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Passenger occupancy increases the potential generation of airborne particles, including SARS-CoV-2-laden particles if infectious passengers are present.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_88</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Passengers can increase SARS-CoV-2 transmission risk in the carriage by emitting infectious particles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_88</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MASKED MANIKINS" target="3D TURBULENT AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d7">MASKED MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d8">3D TURBULENT AIRFLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The masked manikins represent occupied passenger locations whose presence and breathing can affect local airflow around passengers, although the initial ventilation-only solution is not influenced by mask wearing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.62</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MASKED MANIKINS" target="RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">MASKED MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d8">RAILWAY COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">Masked manikins serve as simulated occupants within the rail coach for the dispersion simulations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.62</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_83</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ALTERNATIVE BLOWING OR EXTRACTING AIR VENTS" target="RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">ALTERNATIVE BLOWING OR EXTRACTING AIR VENTS</data>
      <data key="d8">RAIL COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Alternative blowing or extracting vent configurations could connect to different rail coach designs in other simulations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.55</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_55</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS" target="BUOYANT FREE CONVECTION">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d8">BUOYANT FREE CONVECTION</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The warm passenger manikins increase buoyancy-driven free convection because their heads and masks are warmer than the surrounding coach surfaces.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_56</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS" target="RESPIRATORY AEROSOLS AND DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d8">RESPIRATORY DROPS AND DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The modeled passengers are sources of breathing or other respiratory dissemination events that introduce respiratory drops and droplets into the railway coach.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_67</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS" target="INFECTIOUS AGENTS">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d8">INFECTIOUS AGENTS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Because passengers can emit respiratory particles that may carry infectious material, the modeled occupancy increases the potential burden of airborne infectious agents under the simulated respiratory-event scenarios.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_67</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS" target="BUOYANT PASSENGER PLUMES">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d8">BUOYANT PASSENGER PLUMES</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The heat-emitting manikins generate buoyant thermal plumes, so the occupant load contributes to this air distribution pattern.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_67</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS" target="FREE CONVECTION AROUND MANIKINS">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS REPRESENTED BY HUMANOID MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d8">FREE CONVECTION AROUND MANIKINS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence of warm passenger manikins produces free-convection airflow around their bodies.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_67</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BUOYANT FREE CONVECTION" target="ANISOTHERMAL FLOW">
      <data key="d7">BUOYANT FREE CONVECTION</data>
      <data key="d8">ANISOTHERMAL AIRFLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Buoyant free convection is one of the thermal phenomena contributing to the overall anisothermal airflow in the coach.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_56</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION AT THE ENDS OF THE RAIL COACH" target="RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION AT THE ENDS OF THE RAIL COACH</data>
      <data key="d8">RAIL COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The ventilation source serves the rail coach by driving air movement within the carriage, particularly the visible lateral airflow in the lower part near the coach ends.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LATERAL AIRFLOWS FROM VENTILATION" target="VENTILATION AT THE ENDS OF THE RAIL COACH">
      <data key="d7">LATERAL AIRFLOWS FROM VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">VENTILATION AT THE ENDS OF THE RAIL COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The lower-level lateral airflow paths are directly connected to the ventilation source at the ends of the rail coach.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LATERAL AIRFLOWS FROM VENTILATION" target="RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">LATERAL AIRFLOWS FROM VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">RAIL COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The ventilation-driven lateral airflow paths extend through the lower part of the rail coach and contribute to the internal air movement pattern.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
