    <edge source="HUMANOID MANIKINS REPRESENTING TRAIN PASSENGERS" target="BUOYANT PLUME ABOVE THE PASSENGERS">
      <data key="d7">HUMANOID MANIKINS REPRESENTING TRAIN PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">BUOYANT PLUME ABOVE THE PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The passenger manikins act as heat sources, increasing buoyant plume formation through free convection above the occupied row.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BUOYANT PLUME ABOVE THE PASSENGERS" target="FREE-CONVECTION ASCENDING CURRENT">
      <data key="d7">BUOYANT PLUME ABOVE THE PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">FREE-CONVECTION ASCENDING CURRENT</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The buoyant plume is connected to the free-convection ascending current, which rises above the passengers at approximately 0.1 m s−1.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.91</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FREE-CONVECTION ASCENDING CURRENT" target="SLIGHTLY WARMER UPPER AIR LAYER">
      <data key="d7">FREE-CONVECTION ASCENDING CURRENT</data>
      <data key="d8">SLIGHTLY WARMER UPPER AIR LAYER</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The upward free-convection current transports warmer air toward the upper part of the carriage, contributing to the observed slightly warmer upper air layer.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INFECTED BREATHING PASSENGER" target="ONE MICROMETER EXHALED DROPLETS">
