      <data key="d8">EXHALED DROPLET CLOUD</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence of the spreader as an occupant generates the exhaled droplet cloud tracked in the dispersion simulation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_60</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BUOYANT UPWARD PLUME" target="EXHALED DROPLET CLOUD">
      <data key="d7">BUOYANT UPWARD PLUME</data>
      <data key="d8">EXHALED DROPLET CLOUD</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The upward convective plume affects droplet dispersion by rapidly carrying exhaled droplets toward the upper part of the coach.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_60</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UPPER WARM-AIR EXTRACTION PATHWAY" target="CEILING AIR EXTRACTION VENTS">
      <data key="d7">UPPER WARM-AIR EXTRACTION PATHWAY</data>
      <data key="d8">CEILING AIR EXTRACTION VENTS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The upper warm-air pathway connects accumulated droplets in the upper coach layer to the ceiling extraction vents.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_60</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UPPER CEILING REGION OF RAILWAY COACH" target="AIR EXTRACTORS">
      <data key="d7">UPPER CEILING REGION OF RAILWAY COACH</data>
      <data key="d8">AIR EXTRACTORS</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The upper ceiling region is adjacent to or contains the air extractors identified in the text as the removal points for accumulated droplets.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR EXTRACTORS" target="RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">AIR EXTRACTORS</data>
      <data key="d8">RAILWAY COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The air extractors serve the railway coach as part of the ventilation system, removing air and droplets from the indoor space.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR EXTRACTORS" target="UPPER CEILING REGION OF RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">AIR EXTRACTORS</data>
      <data key="d8">UPPER CEILING REGION OF RAILWAY COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The extractors are located near the ceiling and remove droplets that accumulate in the upper part of the coach when thermal effects are taken into account.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR EXTRACTORS" target="RAILWAY TRANSPORT COACH">
      <data key="d7">AIR EXTRACTIONS</data>
      <data key="d8">RAILWAY TRANSPORT COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The extraction system serves the railway coach by exhausting air and airborne contaminants. The observed risk reduction depends on placing these extractions at the ceiling of the coach.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_69</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR EXTRACTORS" target="CONFINED ENVIRONMENTS">
      <data key="d7">AIR EXTRACTIONS</data>
      <data key="d8">CONFINED ENVIRONMENTS</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">Upper-level air extractions are relevant for confined environments such as public transport, professional premises, and schools because aerosols can be carried upward by buoyant plumes.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_69</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BOTTOM TO TOP FLOW PATH" target="SEATED PASSENGER OCCUPIED LOWER REGION">
      <data key="d7">BOTTOM TO TOP FLOW PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">SEATED PASSENGER OCCUPIED LOWER REGION</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The upward airflow path begins in or passes through the lower occupied region where seated passengers are located before carrying droplets upward.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BOTTOM TO TOP FLOW PATH" target="UPPER CEILING REGION OF RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">BOTTOM TO TOP FLOW PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">UPPER CEILING REGION OF RAILWAY COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The bottom-to-top airflow path connects the lower occupied area to the upper ceiling region where droplets accumulate under the thermal-effects case.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BOTTOM TO TOP FLOW PATH" target="AIR EXTRACTORS">
      <data key="d7">BOTTOM TO TOP FLOW PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">AIR EXTRACTORS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The upward airflow path leads toward the ceiling air extractors, enabling rapid elimination of droplets accumulated near the ceiling.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EXHALED CONTAMINATING DROPLETS AND AEROSOLS" target="LARGER VOLUME DROPLET DISPERSION WITHOUT THERMAL EFFECTS">
      <data key="d7">EXHALED CONTAMINATING DROPLETS AND AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d8">LARGER VOLUME DROPLET DISPERSION WITHOUT THERMAL EFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">When thermal effects are ignored, the exhaled droplets and aerosols exhibit a broader distribution, appearing more numerous and occupying a larger coach volume.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EXHALED CONTAMINATING DROPLETS AND AEROSOLS" target="UPPER PART DROPLET ACCUMULATION WITH THERMAL EFFECTS">
      <data key="d7">EXHALED CONTAMINATING DROPLETS AND AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d8">UPPER PART DROPLET ACCUMULATION WITH THERMAL EFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">When thermal effects are included, the exhaled droplets and aerosols mainly accumulate in the upper part of the coach near the ceiling extractors.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.91</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UPPER PART DROPLET ACCUMULATION WITH THERMAL EFFECTS" target="UPPER CEILING REGION OF RAILWAY COACH">
      <data key="d7">UPPER PART DROPLET ACCUMULATION WITH THERMAL EFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d8">UPPER CEILING REGION OF RAILWAY COACH</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The thermal-effects droplet pattern is spatially associated with the upper ceiling region where the contaminating droplets accumulate.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
