      <data key="d7">SPREADER</data>
      <data key="d8">EXHALED CONTAMINATING DROPLETS AND AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The spreader increases the airborne contaminant load by exhaling droplets and aerosols that may carry pathogenic biological agents.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SEATED PASSENGERS" target="SEATED PASSENGER OCCUPIED LOWER REGION">
      <data key="d7">SEATED PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">SEATED PASSENGER OCCUPIED LOWER REGION</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The seated passengers are located in the lower occupied region of the coach, which is relevant to their reduced exposure when droplets concentrate near the ceiling.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_61</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="RAILWAY COACH INTERIOR" target="THERMALLY INFLUENCED DROPLET DISPERSION PATTERN">
      <data key="d7">RAILWAY COACH INTERIOR</data>
      <data key="d8">THERMALLY INFLUENCED DROPLET DISPERSION PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The railway coach interior has a modeled droplet distribution pattern; including thermal effects changes this pattern and is reported to reduce the number of suspended droplets.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_62</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="RAILWAY COACH INTERIOR" target="TURBULENT AIRFLOW AND RESPIRATORY DROPLET DISPERSION">
      <data key="d7">RAILWAY COACH INTERIOR</data>
      <data key="d8">TURBULENT AIRFLOW AND RESPIRATORY DROPLET DISPERSION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The ventilated coach interior is characterized by the simulated turbulent airflow and respiratory-droplet dispersion pattern.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_64</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DISSEMINATING PASSENGER" target="SARS-COV-2-LADEN RESPIRATORY DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">DISSEMINATING PASSENGER</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2-LADEN RESPIRATORY DROPLETS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The disseminating passenger is the source of respiratory droplets carrying SARS-CoV-2, increasing the airborne contaminant load in the coach; wearing a surgical mask reduces this source during exhalation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_62</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EXHALATION PLUME FROM SPREADER" target="RAILWAY COACH INTERIOR">
      <data key="d7">EXHALATION PLUME FROM SPREADER</data>
      <data key="d8">RAILWAY COACH INTERIOR</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The spreader's exhalation plume carries droplets from the passenger into the enclosed railway coach interior.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_62</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UPPER PART OF RAILWAY COACH" target="VENTILATION">
      <data key="d7">UPPER PART OF RAILWAY COACH</data>
      <data key="d8">VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">After droplets rise to the upper part of the railway coach, they are carried away by the ventilation.</data>
