    <edge source="50% EXTRACTION THROUGH COMPARTMENT #2" target="END-TO-MIDDLE AIRFLOW PATTERN">
      <data key="d7">50% EXTRACTION THROUGH COMPARTMENT #2</data>
      <data key="d8">END-TO-MIDDLE AIRFLOW PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The concentration of extraction through compartment #2 helps establish the intended movement of air from the ends of the coach toward the middle.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_90</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LOW-VELOCITY SUPPLY AND EXTRACTION CONDITION" target="END-TO-MIDDLE AIRFLOW PATTERN">
      <data key="d7">LOW-VELOCITY SUPPLY AND EXTRACTION CONDITION</data>
      <data key="d8">END-TO-MIDDLE AIRFLOW PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The end-to-middle airflow pattern is implemented while keeping supply and extraction velocities below 0.2 m s−1 for comfort.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.74</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_90</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ATMOSPHERIC PRESSURE AIRFLOW BALANCE" target="END-TO-MIDDLE AIRFLOW PATTERN">
      <data key="d7">ATMOSPHERIC PRESSURE AIRFLOW BALANCE</data>
      <data key="d8">END-TO-MIDDLE AIRFLOW PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">The end-to-middle airflow pattern operates within the overall atmospheric-pressure balance between compartments.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_90</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UNMASKED MOUTH BREATHING AIR PATH" target="DIRECT ORAL BREATHING DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">UNMASKED MOUTH BREATHING AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">DIRECT ORAL BREATHING DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">In the no-mask base case, breathing air passes directly through the mouth, producing a direct oral airflow distribution.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_91</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FITTED-MASK FILTRATION AIR PATH" target="POROUS MASK DIFFUSION DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">FITTED-MASK FILTRATION AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">POROUS MASK DIFFUSION DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">With a perfectly fitted mask, emitted air is slowed and diffused through the porous filtering material, with no leakage around the face-mask interface.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_91</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FITTED-MASK FILTRATION AIR PATH" target="RESPIRATORY PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">FITTED-MASK FILTRATION AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">RESPIRATORY PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Respiratory particles carried by the emitted air may pass through the filtering part if not retained by the fitted mask.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_91</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LOOSE-MASK LEAKAGE AIR PATH" target="FACE-MASK LEAK DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">LOOSE-MASK LEAKAGE AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">FACE-MASK LEAK DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">With a loosely worn mask, leaks between the face and mask create an additional airflow distribution that can bypass the filtering surface.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_91</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LOOSE-MASK LEAKAGE AIR PATH" target="RESPIRATORY PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">LOOSE-MASK LEAKAGE AIR PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">RESPIRATORY PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Respiratory particles may be transported along leakage paths when the mask is loose, in addition to any particles passing through the filter.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_91</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INFECTED HUMANOID MANIKIN" target="SARS-COV-2 VIRUS">
      <data key="d7">INFECTED HUMANOID MANIKIN</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The infected manikin acts as an occupant source that releases respiratory droplets presumed to carry a pathogen such as SARS-CoV-2 during breathing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INFECTED HUMANOID MANIKIN" target="NORMAL BREATHING">
      <data key="d7">INFECTED HUMANOID MANIKIN</data>
      <data key="d8">NORMAL BREATHING</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The manikin is modeled as breathing normally, with droplet release repeated at each breathing cycle.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NORMAL BREATHING" target="NO-MASK EXHALATION FLOW">
      <data key="d7">NORMAL BREATHING</data>
      <data key="d8">NO-MASK EXHALATION FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The no-mask exhalation flow is one configuration-specific realization of the normal breathing dissemination event. | The loose-mask exhalation flow is a configuration-specific realization of the normal breathing dissemination event with both filtered and leakage outlet paths.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.58</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NORMAL BREATHING" target="WELL-FITTED MASK EXHALATION FLOW">
      <data key="d7">NORMAL BREATHING</data>
      <data key="d8">WELL-FITTED MASK EXHALATION FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The well-fitted mask exhalation flow is a configuration-specific realization of the normal breathing dissemination event.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.55</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MOUTH BOUNDARY" target="NORMAL BREATHING">
      <data key="d7">MOUTH BOUNDARY</data>
      <data key="d8">NORMAL BREATHING</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The mouth boundary is the simulation-domain boundary where breathing boundary conditions are imposed for the exhalation event.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MOUTH BOUNDARY" target="FILTERING PART OF THE MASK">
      <data key="d7">MOUTH BOUNDARY</data>
      <data key="d8">FILTERING PART OF THE MASK</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">In masked configurations, exhaled air and particles from the mouth can pass to the filtering part of the mask if they are not retained.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MOUTH BOUNDARY" target="LEAKAGE SURFACES ON MASK EDGES">
      <data key="d7">MOUTH BOUNDARY</data>
      <data key="d8">LEAKAGE SURFACES ON MASK EDGES</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">In the loose-mask configuration, exhaled air and particles from the mouth can also exit through leakage surfaces at the mask edges.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MOUTH BOUNDARY" target="NO-MASK EXHALATION FLOW">
      <data key="d7">MOUTH BOUNDARY</data>
      <data key="d8">NO-MASK EXHALATION FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">When no mask is worn, the mouth boundary directly produces the exhalation flow carrying droplets into the surrounding air.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.68</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FILTERING PART OF THE MASK" target="WELL-FITTED MASK EXHALATION FLOW">
      <data key="d7">FILTERING PART OF THE MASK</data>
      <data key="d8">WELL-FITTED MASK EXHALATION FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">In the perfectly fitted mask case, the filtering part governs the outlet airflow pattern because air and particles not retained by the mask pass through the filter.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FILTERING PART OF THE MASK" target="NO-MASK EXHALATION FLOW">
      <data key="d7">FILTERING PART OF THE MASK</data>
      <data key="d8">LOOSE-MASK EXHALATION FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">In the loose-mask case, the filtering part remains one of the outlet paths contributing to the exhalation airflow pattern.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.68</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LEAKAGE SURFACES ON MASK EDGES" target="NO-MASK EXHALATION FLOW">
      <data key="d7">LEAKAGE SURFACES ON MASK EDGES</data>
      <data key="d8">LOOSE-MASK EXHALATION FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">In the loose-mask case, leakage surfaces at the mask edges contribute to the exhalation airflow pattern by allowing air and particles to bypass the filtering material.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NOSE LEAK ZONE" target="LEAKAGE SURFACES ON MASK EDGES">
      <data key="d7">NOSE LEAK ZONE</data>
      <data key="d8">LEAKAGE SURFACES ON MASK EDGES</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The nose leak zone is one of the leakage surfaces considered at the mask edge in the loose-mask case.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.65</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d14">6ce6bcdd-6339-49d0-abf2-8f8a9a51aa42</data>
    </edge>
