      <data key="d8">DOOR-OPEN AIRFLOW PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Frequent passenger boarding and alighting during operation can increase disturbance to the cabin airflow dynamics and contribute to the door-open airflow pattern.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HUMAN CONTACT FREQUENCY" target="BIOAEROSOL">
      <data key="d7">HUMAN CONTACT FREQUENCY</data>
      <data key="d8">BIOAEROSOL</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Higher human contact frequency can increase the practical opportunity for transmission from viable microorganisms carried in bioaerosols, even though actual risk also depends on viability and inactivation rate.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.62</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CABIN / COMPARTMENT" target="PLATFORM">
      <data key="d7">CABIN / COMPARTMENT</data>
      <data key="d8">PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The compartment and platform are adjacent spaces across the vehicle door. Door opening enables direct air exchange between them.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CABIN / COMPARTMENT" target="AIRFLOW PATTERN">
      <data key="d7">CABIN / COMPARTMENT</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRFLOW PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The cabin/compartment has an airflow pattern that changes when the vehicle door opens, causing part of the airflow to move directly outside.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CABIN / COMPARTMENT" target="CABIN PRESSURE FIELD">
      <data key="d7">CABIN / COMPARTMENT</data>
      <data key="d8">CABIN PRESSURE FIELD</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_PRESSURE</data>
      <data key="d10">The cabin/compartment has a pressure field that is altered by door opening. This change contributes to airflow redistribution and outward bioaerosol transport.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VEHICLE DOOR" target="CABIN / COMPARTMENT">
      <data key="d7">VEHICLE DOOR</data>
      <data key="d8">CABIN / COMPARTMENT</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The vehicle door is the opening connected to the cabin/compartment. When open, it permits compartment air and bioaerosols to move outward.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VEHICLE DOOR" target="PLATFORM">
      <data key="d7">VEHICLE DOOR</data>
      <data key="d8">PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The vehicle door connects the internal compartment with the platform-side external area, enabling escaped bioaerosols to reach passengers outside.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VEHICLE DOOR" target="BIOAEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">VEHICLE DOOR</data>
      <data key="d8">BIOAEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The open vehicle door provides the escape path for bioaerosols moving from the compartment toward the platform.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CABIN PRESSURE FIELD" target="BIOAEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">CABIN PRESSURE FIELD</data>
      <data key="d8">BIOAEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">The pressure field affects the containment of bioaerosols inside the cabin/compartment. When the door opens, changed pressure conditions reduce containment and support outward escape.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.73</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MEASUREMENT POINT M1 OUTSIDE COMPARTMENT" target="PLATFORM">
      <data key="d7">MEASUREMENT POINT M1 OUTSIDE COMPARTMENT</data>
      <data key="d8">PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">M1 is located outside the compartment near the door, corresponding to the platform-side region where escaped bioaerosols may be present.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.66</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MEASUREMENT POINT M1 OUTSIDE COMPARTMENT" target="CABIN / COMPARTMENT">
      <data key="d7">MEASUREMENT POINT E1 INSIDE COMPARTMENT</data>
      <data key="d8">CABIN / COMPARTMENT</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">E1 is located inside the compartment and provides the internal reference measurement for airborne S. aureus.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.64</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MEASUREMENT POINT M1 OUTSIDE COMPARTMENT" target="S. AUREUS">
      <data key="d7">MEASUREMENT POINT M1 OUTSIDE COMPARTMENT</data>
      <data key="d8">S. AUREUS</data>
      <data key="d9">PRESSURE_CONTAINS</data>
      <data key="d10">S. aureus was detected at outside measurement point M1 at about 35.89% of the amount found at internal point E1, indicating pathogen escape through the door. | Internal measurement point E1 contained the reference amount of S. aureus used to compare the level detected outside at M1.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.69</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PASSENGERS ON THE PLATFORM" target="BIOAEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">PASSENGERS ON THE PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d8">BIOAEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Passengers occupying the platform increase the potential exposure consequence of bioaerosol escape, because escaped particles may be inhaled during brief contact near the subway door.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.61</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CABIN ENVIRONMENT" target="FRESH AIR DILUTION EFFECT">
      <data key="d7">CABIN ENVIRONMENT</data>
      <data key="d8">FRESH AIR DILUTION EFFECT</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The cabin environment exhibits a fresh-air dilution pattern under standard ventilation modes, establishing the baseline condition for comparison with active purification devices.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.58</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BREATHING ZONE OF SEATED PASSENGERS" target="RESPIRATORY PATHOGENS">
      <data key="d7">BREATHING ZONE OF SEATED PASSENGERS</data>
      <data key="d8">RESPIRATORY PATHOGENS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The breathing zone of seated passengers is the exposure location where respiratory pathogen inhalation risk is discussed. This relationship represents the occupancy-linked exposure concern, not a claim that passengers generated additional pathogens.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.48</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="STANDARD VENTILATION MODES" target="CABIN ENVIRONMENT">
      <data key="d7">STANDARD VENTILATION MODES</data>
      <data key="d8">CABIN ENVIRONMENT</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">Standard ventilation modes serve the cabin environment by providing baseline fresh-air dilution, which was used as the comparison case for the IFD filter and CP generator.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="STANDARD VENTILATION MODES" target="FRESH AIR DILUTION EFFECT">
      <data key="d7">STANDARD VENTILATION MODES</data>
      <data key="d8">FRESH AIR DILUTION EFFECT</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The standard ventilation modes produce the fresh-air dilution effect used as the baseline air distribution and contaminant dilution condition.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.64</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SUBWAY CARRIAGE OCCUPIED AIRSPACE" target="CONSTRAINED AIRFLOW CIRCULATION">
      <data key="d7">SUBWAY CARRIAGE OCCUPIED AIRSPACE</data>
      <data key="d8">CONSTRAINED AIRFLOW CIRCULATION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The subway carriage occupied airspace has a constrained airflow circulation pattern due to its spacious structure. This pattern reduces how efficiently particles are delivered to filtration or purification devices.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SUBWAY CARRIAGE OCCUPIED AIRSPACE" target="STAGNANT AREAS">
      <data key="d7">SUBWAY CARRIAGE OCCUPIED AIRSPACE</data>
      <data key="d8">STAGNANT AREAS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The carriage contains stagnant areas that represent poor air-mixing regions. These regions hinder efficient filtration by limiting particle transport to active purification systems.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.83</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEM EQUIPPED WITH A PURIFIER" target="SUBWAY CARRIAGE OCCUPIED AIRSPACE">
      <data key="d7">AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEM EQUIPPED WITH A PURIFIER</data>
      <data key="d8">SUBWAY CARRIAGE OCCUPIED AIRSPACE</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The purifier-equipped air-conditioning system serves the subway carriage by attempting to remove airborne particles from recirculated carriage air, although its effectiveness is limited when particles disperse before entering the system.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONSTRAINED AIRFLOW CIRCULATION" target="RELEASED AIRBORNE PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">CONSTRAINED AIRFLOW CIRCULATION</data>
      <data key="d8">RELEASED AIRBORNE PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The constrained circulation pattern affects the movement of released airborne particles, allowing them to disperse through the carriage rather than rapidly entering the purifier-equipped air-conditioning system.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="STAGNANT AREAS" target="RELEASED AIRBORNE PARTICLES">
      <data key="d7">STAGNANT AREAS</data>
      <data key="d8">RELEASED AIRBORNE PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Stagnant areas are associated with particle retention or delayed transport, which can hinder the efficient filtration of released airborne particles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="RETURN AIR" target="MIXING CHAMBER">
      <data key="d7">RETURN AIR</data>
      <data key="d8">MIXING CHAMBER</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Return air passes through the mixing chamber as one of the air streams treated by the IFD filter.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIRFLOW ORGANIZATION" target="INDOOR AEROSOL TRANSMISSION PATTERNS">
      <data key="d7">AIRFLOW ORGANIZATION</data>
      <data key="d8">BIOAEROSOL TRANSMISSION PATTERNS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Airflow organization is connected to bioaerosol transmission patterns because organized airflow affects how airborne biological particles move through the cabin.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CABIN RESOURCE LOCATIONS" target="INDOOR AEROSOL TRANSMISSION PATTERNS">
      <data key="d7">CABIN RESOURCE LOCATIONS</data>
      <data key="d8">BIOAEROSOL TRANSMISSION PATTERNS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The locations of resources within the cabin may introduce variations in bioaerosol transmission patterns under actual operating conditions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.66</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN" target="COUPLED CABIN FLOW FIELDS">
      <data key="d7">TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN</data>
      <data key="d8">COUPLED CABIN FLOW FIELDS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The subway cabin contains coupled airflow fields that shape bioaerosol dispersion. These multiple flow fields are described as driving aerosol movement throughout the cabin.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN" target="AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION">
      <data key="d7">TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The subway cabin exhibits airborne transmission as a primary aerosol propagation mode. Air and sediment sampling methods were used to identify this mode of indoor bioaerosol spread.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN" target="RELATIVELY UNIFORM BIOAEROSOL DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN</data>
      <data key="d8">RELATIVELY UNIFORM BIOAEROSOL DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The cabin exhibits a relatively uniform bioaerosol distribution, with less than 10% concentration difference between the two ends of the cabin under the reported conditions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN" target="SURFACE DEPOSITION ON AISLES, SEATS, AND WINDOWS">
      <data key="d7">TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN</data>
      <data key="d8">SURFACE DEPOSITION ON AISLES, SEATS, AND WINDOWS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The cabin also exhibits bioaerosol deposition onto internal surfaces at varying heights, including aisles, seats, and windows, indicating a possible contact-transmission pathway.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN" target="FLOW CHARACTERISTICS OF SMALL-SIZE AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN</data>
      <data key="d8">FLOW CHARACTERISTICS OF SMALL-SIZE AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The cabin environment includes small-aerosol transport behavior shaped by indoor airflow and multiple obstacles, which is relevant to exposure assessment.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN" target="TRANSMISSION-PATTERN VARIABILITY">
      <data key="d7">TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN</data>
      <data key="d8">TRANSMISSION-PATTERN VARIABILITY</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">In actual subway-cabin scenarios, distribution and transmission patterns may vary because of occupancy behavior and resource-placement conditions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.66</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TWO DESIGNED AIR PURIFICATION DEVICES" target="TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN">
      <data key="d7">TWO DESIGNED AIR PURIFICATION DEVICES</data>
      <data key="d8">TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The air purification devices serve the subway cabin by treating cabin air and reducing bioaerosol spread. The study evaluates their individual and combined performance in the enclosed transportation environment.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CABIN INTERIOR SURFACE ZONES" target="TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN">
      <data key="d7">CABIN INTERIOR SURFACE ZONES</data>
      <data key="d8">TYPICAL SUBWAY CABIN</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Aisles, seats, and windows are interior surface zones adjacent to the cabin air volume where airborne bioaerosols may deposit.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d14">92822355-ab82-4e40-9fca-0876f2fc943e</data>
    </edge>
