      <data key="d8">36 ACH</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The unoccupied room has a stated mechanical ventilation rate of 36 ACH based on supply airflow and room volume. This rate is used as N in the Far-UVC equivalent air-change equation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UNOCCUPIED ROOM" target="EQUIVALENT AIR CHANGE RATE DUE TO FAR-UVC">
      <data key="d7">UNOCCUPIED ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">EQUIVALENT AIR CHANGE RATE DUE TO FAR-UVC</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The room is assigned an additional equivalent air change rate due to Far-UVC, representing ultraviolet virus inactivation expressed as a ventilation-equivalent removal rate.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR CHANGES PER HOUR OF THE TRACER (ACHT)" target="CARBON DIOXIDE">
      <data key="d7">AIR CHANGES PER HOUR OF THE TRACER (ACHT)</data>
      <data key="d8">CARBON DIOXIDE</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The tracer-derived ACH is determined from, and represents, the ventilation-driven decay of carbon dioxide concentration in the room over time.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EQUIVALENT AIR CHANGE RATE DUE TO FAR-UVC" target="ACTIVE VIRUS">
      <data key="d7">EQUIVALENT AIR CHANGE RATE DUE TO FAR-UVC</data>
      <data key="d8">ACTIVE VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The Far-UVC equivalent air change rate affects active virus concentration by representing the additional viable-virus reduction observed when Far-UVC lamps are on compared with lamps off.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE" target="ACTUAL VENTILATION RATE, N">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE</data>
      <data key="d8">ACTUAL VENTILATION RATE, N</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The room has an actual ventilation rate, N, based on supply airflow and room volume before any correction for imperfect mixing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE" target="EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE</data>
      <data key="d8">EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The room has an effective ventilation rate, N', which accounts for incomplete mixing by applying the mixing factor K to the actual ventilation rate.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE" target="EQUIVALENT AIR CHANGE RATE DUE TO FAR-UVC, NUV">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE</data>
      <data key="d8">EQUIVALENT AIR CHANGE RATE DUE TO FAR-UVC, NUV</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The room is assigned an equivalent air change rate due to Far-UVC, representing UVC-driven airborne inactivation as ventilation-equivalent removal.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.89</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE" target="WELL-MIXED CONDITION">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE</data>
      <data key="d8">WELL-MIXED ROOM CONDITION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The referenced derivation assumes the room follows a well-mixed, steady-state air distribution condition.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE" target="MIXING FACTOR, K">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATED ROOM OR SPACE</data>
      <data key="d8">MIXING FACTOR, K</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The room's incomplete mixing is represented using the mixing factor K, which indicates ventilation efficacy within the space.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.91</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EQUIVALENT AIR CHANGE RATE DUE TO FAR-UVC, NUV" target="POXVIRUSES">
      <data key="d7">EQUIVALENT AIR CHANGE RATE DUE TO FAR-UVC, NUV</data>
      <data key="d8">POXVIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The UVC-equivalent air change rate represents airborne pathogen inactivation as an air-change-equivalent removal process; the cited derivation is based on UVC inactivation of poxviruses in a simulated hospital room environment.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.83</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ACTUAL VENTILATION RATE, N" target="EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'">
      <data key="d7">ACTUAL VENTILATION RATE, N</data>
      <data key="d8">EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The effective ventilation rate is calculated from the actual ventilation rate using N' = N/K, so changes in N directly affect N'.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'" target="POXVIRUSES">
      <data key="d7">EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'</data>
      <data key="d8">POXVIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The effective ventilation rate affects airborne pathogen dilution and removal after accounting for incomplete room mixing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MIXING FACTOR, K" target="PERFECT MIXING">
      <data key="d7">MIXING FACTOR, K</data>
      <data key="d8">PERFECT MIXING</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">A K value of 1 corresponds to perfect mixing, where room air is ideally mixed and effective ventilation equals actual ventilation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MIXING FACTOR, K" target="POORLY MIXED ROOM CONDITION">
      <data key="d7">MIXING FACTOR, K</data>
      <data key="d8">POORLY MIXED ROOM CONDITION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">High K values, up to about 10, correspond to poorly mixed room conditions and indicate reduced ventilation effectiveness.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MIXING FACTOR, K" target="EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'">
      <data key="d7">MIXING FACTOR, K</data>
      <data key="d8">EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The mixing factor modifies the actual ventilation rate to produce the effective ventilation rate; larger K values reduce N' for a given N.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PERFECT MIXING" target="EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'">
      <data key="d7">PERFECT MIXING</data>
      <data key="d8">EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Under perfect mixing, K = 1, so the effective ventilation rate equals the actual ventilation rate.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="POORLY MIXED ROOM CONDITION" target="EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'">
      <data key="d7">POORLY MIXED ROOM CONDITION</data>
      <data key="d8">EFFECTIVE VENTILATION RATE, N'</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Poor mixing increases K and therefore lowers the effective ventilation rate relative to the actual ventilation rate.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d14">d8e5e6fb-91d7-40aa-8229-b92309abbaff</data>
    </edge>
