      <data key="d8">INFECTIOUS SARS-COV-2 AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Different air exchange rates affected the dilution, persistence, and removal of infectious SARS-CoV-2 aerosols in the indoor event environment.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR EXCHANGE RATE CONDITIONS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">AIR EXCHANGE RATE CONDITIONS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">By affecting aerosol concentration and removal, air exchange conditions influenced the exposure risk associated with airborne SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
