      <data key="d7">SUSCEPTIBLE POPULATION</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Because seroprevalence was assumed negligible, most people were susceptible to infection; a larger susceptible occupancy load increases the potential impact of SARS-CoV-2 exposure during mass gathering events.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.72</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="100,000 PARTICIPANTS PER MONTH" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">100,000 PARTICIPANTS PER MONTH</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">This participant-load condition still contributes to modeled SARS-CoV-2 transmission opportunities during mass gatherings, although the text notes that expected case counts are lower than for larger events.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.6</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="200,000 PARTICIPANTS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">200,000 PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The larger 200,000-participant mass-gathering condition is associated with increased SARS-CoV-2 positive cases attributed to the event, especially without masks and with non-optimal ventilation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
