      <data key="d7">VV1 BETTER VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The better ventilation condition is associated with reduced SARS-CoV-2 infection estimates; for example, with masks and favorable conditions, predicted excess cases are lower than under VV2.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VV2 NON-OPTIMAL VENTILATION" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">VV2 NON-OPTIMAL VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The non-optimal ventilation condition is associated with higher SARS-CoV-2 infection estimates and with possible hospitalization or death at higher incidence levels.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BETTER VENTILATION VV1" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">BETTER VENTILATION VV1</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The ventilation condition affects airborne SARS-CoV-2 transmission risk. The text reports that improved ventilation, together with masks, decreases the percentage of cases acquired during mass gathering events and highlights adequate ventilation as important for risk reduction.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="POOR VENTILATION SYSTEMS" target="INDOOR AEROSOL EXPOSURE PATHWAY">
      <data key="d7">POOR VENTILATION SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">INDOOR AEROSOL EXPOSURE PATHWAY</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Poor ventilation, interpreted as inadequate air exchange, increases aerosol accumulation and exposure in indoor mass-gathering settings.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="POOR VENTILATION SYSTEMS" target="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">POOR VENTILATION SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19)</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Poor ventilation substantially increases the risk of SARS-CoV-2 transmission by raising aerosol exposure, which the text says can result in a high number of infections.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HIGH-CONTACT OR NO-PRECAUTION MGE" target="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">HIGH-CONTACT OR NO-PRECAUTION MGE</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19)</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Mass gatherings without precautions or with many contacts can substantially increase SARS-CoV-2 epidemic spread, according to the text.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PHYSICALLY DISTANCED MGE" target="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">PHYSICALLY DISTANCED MGE</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19)</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Physically distanced mass gatherings still involve some indoor contacts, but the occupancy-driven increase in SARS-CoV-2 risk is weak because contact numbers are low and risk depends mainly on ventilation adequacy.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.32</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INDOOR AEROSOL EXPOSURE PATHWAY" target="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">INDOOR AEROSOL EXPOSURE PATHWAY</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19)</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The indoor aerosol pathway connects ventilation conditions to airborne SARS-CoV-2 exposure and resulting infection risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SEATED VISITOR OCCUPANCY PERIODS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">SEATED VISITOR OCCUPANCY PERIODS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">When visitors stay seated indoors, exposure time to aerosols can accumulate, increasing the opportunity for SARS-CoV-2 transmission if protective measures such as masks are not maintained.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HIGH-ATTENDANCE MASS GATHERING EVENT" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">HIGH-ATTENDANCE MASS GATHERING EVENT</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">A mass gathering involving thousands of people creates a large occupancy burden and increases the need for testing, hygiene organization, and compliance measures to reduce SARS-CoV-2 transmission risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.58</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ENTRY HALF-TIME AND EXIT CROWDING PHASES" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">ENTRY HALF-TIME AND EXIT CROWDING PHASES</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Entry, half-time, and exit phases involve attendee contacts that can contribute to SARS-CoV-2 transmission risk, although the text characterizes these as comparatively short-duration and less critical than prolonged seated exposure.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.44</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SPECTATOR AREA" target="ASHRAE STANDARD 62.1-2013 MINIMUM VENTILATION RATE OF 3.8 L S-1 PER PERSON">
      <data key="d7">SPECTATOR AREA</data>
      <data key="d8">ASHRAE STANDARD 62.1-2013 MINIMUM VENTILATION RATE OF 3.8 L S-1 PER PERSON</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The ASHRAE Standard 62.1-2013 recommendation applies to the spectator area as the minimum ventilation benchmark of 3.8 l s-1 per person.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SPECTATOR AREA" target="SEATED VENTILATION RATE OF 6.7 L S-1 PER PERSON">
      <data key="d7">SPECTATOR AREA</data>
      <data key="d8">SEATED VENTILATION RATE OF 6.7 L S-1 PER PERSON</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">Under the maximum seated occupancy of 8,200 persons, the spectator area has a calculated per-person ventilation rate of 6.7 l s-1 per person. | Under the maximum standing occupancy of 12,300 persons, the spectator area has a calculated per-person ventilation rate of 4.5 l s-1 per person.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LEIPZIG ARENA AIR SUPPLY OF 198,000 M3 H-1" target="SPECTATOR AREA">
      <data key="d7">LEIPZIG ARENA AIR SUPPLY OF 198,000 M3 H-1</data>
      <data key="d8">SPECTATOR AREA</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The Leipzig arena air-supply system provides ventilation to the spectator area, enabling the calculated per-person ventilation rates for seated and standing occupancy conditions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SEATED VENTILATION RATE OF 6.7 L S-1 PER PERSON" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">SEATED VENTILATION RATE OF 6.7 L S-1 PER PERSON</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation is described as crucial for risk associated with mass gathering events. The higher seated per-person ventilation rate can affect aerosol-related SARS-CoV-2 exposure risk in the spectator area. | The standing configuration provides lower per-person ventilation than the seated configuration, which can affect aerosol-related SARS-CoV-2 exposure risk during mass gathering events.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MAXIMUM 8,200 SEATED PERSON OCCUPANCY" target="SEATED VENTILATION RATE OF 6.7 L S-1 PER PERSON">
      <data key="d7">MAXIMUM 8,200 SEATED PERSON OCCUPANCY</data>
      <data key="d8">SEATED VENTILATION RATE OF 6.7 L S-1 PER PERSON</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The seated occupancy load is the denominator used to calculate the seated per-person ventilation rate. The relationship captures that occupant load directly determines the resulting per-person ventilation level.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MAXIMUM 12,300 STANDING PERSON OCCUPANCY" target="SEATED VENTILATION RATE OF 6.7 L S-1 PER PERSON">
      <data key="d7">MAXIMUM 12,300 STANDING PERSON OCCUPANCY</data>
      <data key="d8">STANDING VENTILATION RATE OF 4.5 L S-1 PER PERSON</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The larger standing occupancy load reduces the available ventilation per person to 4.5 l s-1 per person compared with the seated configuration.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MAXIMUM 12,300 STANDING PERSON OCCUPANCY" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">MAXIMUM 12,300 STANDING PERSON OCCUPANCY</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The maximum standing occupancy represents a dense, close-proximity condition with more occupants and lower per-person ventilation, both of which are relevant to potential SARS-CoV-2 exposure risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.73</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LARGER CROWD CONDITIONS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">LARGER CROWD CONDITIONS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The text states that larger crowds can cause closer spacing during entry and that unseated concerts allow visitors to remain in close proximity without fixed positions, increasing contact opportunities relevant to SARS-CoV-2 transmission risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
