      <data key="d7">WELL-VENTILATED AIR DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The well-ventilated indoor air condition is associated with reduced airborne transmission risk for SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.74</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONCERT PARTICIPANT OCCUPANCY" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">CONCERT PARTICIPANT OCCUPANCY</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Participant contacts create opportunities for SARS-CoV-2 transmission; the effect could be higher if the same groups attend multiple events or if additional contacts occur around the event.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA (QIA)" target="AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA (QIA)</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The indoor arena is the built environment for which aerosol movement, indoor aerosol concentrations, and breathing-air concentrations were assessed during the experimental mass gathering event.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INDOOR MASS GATHERING EVENTS (MGE)" target="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">INDOOR MASS GATHERING EVENTS (MGE)</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19)</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">An indoor mass gathering can increase COVID-19 transmission risk by increasing contacts and aerosol exposure among many people. The text qualifies this relationship: with hygiene practices and good ventilation, MGE appear to contribute little to epidemic spread, whereas lack of hygiene and/or inadequate ventilation increases the number of subjects at risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PARTICIPANTS" target="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19)</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence of participants creates contact opportunities and breathing-air exposure relevant to COVID-19 transmission. The study measured these contacts with contact tracing devices and integrated them into epidemiological simulations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INADEQUATE VENTILATION CONDITIONS" target="SARS-COV-2 / COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">INADEQUATE VENTILATION CONDITIONS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19)</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Inadequate ventilation affects COVID-19 transmission risk by increasing the number of subjects at risk, particularly when hygiene practices are also lacking.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INADEQUATE VENTILATION CONDITIONS" target="AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">INADEQUATE VENTILATION CONDITIONS</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Insufficient ventilation can worsen aerosol distribution and concentration conditions indoors, increasing exposure potential for occupants.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="4000 PLANNED PARTICIPANTS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">4000 PLANNED PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The planned occupancy load of 4000 participants would increase potential airborne SARS-CoV-2 exposure opportunity in the arena if an infectious person were present. The relationship is conditional because the study required pre-event SARS-CoV-2 screening and excluded positive cases.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.52</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="4200 HISTORICAL MEAN EVENT PARTICIPANTS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">4200 HISTORICAL MEAN EVENT PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The historical mean event size of 4200 participants represents a high reference occupancy condition that could increase SARS-CoV-2 exposure opportunity during comparable real events if infectious attendees were present.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.45</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="1212 TOTAL EXPERIMENTAL PARTICIPANTS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">1212 TOTAL EXPERIMENTAL PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The actual experimental participation of 1212 persons created the overall human occupancy load for the study day. This load would increase potential airborne SARS-CoV-2 exposure only if an infectious participant were present despite screening.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.55</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="1192 SCENARIO 1 PARTICIPANTS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">1192 SCENARIO 1 PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The 1192 participants present in Scenario 1 formed a scenario-specific occupancy load that could increase potential SARS-CoV-2 aerosol exposure opportunity compared with a lower-occupancy or empty arena, conditional on the presence of an infectious person. | The 1158 participants present in Scenario 2 formed a scenario-specific occupancy load that could increase potential airborne SARS-CoV-2 exposure opportunity if an infectious participant were present. | The 1054 participants present in Scenario 3 formed the lowest scenario-specific occupancy load. It would still increase potential SARS-CoV-2 exposure opportunity compared with no occupancy, but less than the higher-occupancy scenarios, assuming an infectious person were present.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.5</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PARTICIPANTS (N = 1212)" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">PARTICIPANTS (N = 1212)</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The participant population constitutes the potential source and receptor pool for SARS-CoV-2 exposure during the event scenarios.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.68</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SCENARIO 1 UNRESTRICTED ARENA OCCUPANCY" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">SCENARIO 1 UNRESTRICTED ARENA OCCUPANCY</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The unrestricted, dense seating arrangement without empty seats between participants and use of only two main entrances/exits creates the least restricted condition and likely the greatest close-contact opportunity among the scenarios.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SCENARIO 2 CHECKERBOARD QUADRANT OCCUPANCY" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">SCENARIO 2 CHECKERBOARD QUADRANT OCCUPANCY</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Scenario 2 still includes an occupied indoor audience and therefore potential SARS-CoV-2 exposure, but checkerboard seating and quadrant restrictions reduce contact and mixing relative to Scenario 1.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.52</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SCENARIO 3 PAIRWISE DISTANCED OCCUPANCY" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">SCENARIO 3 PAIRWISE DISTANCED OCCUPANCY</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Scenario 3 still contains participants who could transmit or be exposed to SARS-CoV-2, but pairwise seating, 1.5 m spacing between occupied pairs, and more entrances/exits indicate the lowest contact intensity of the three scenarios.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.38</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TWO MAIN ENTRANCES AND EXITS" target="INDOOR CONCERT ARENA">
      <data key="d7">TWO MAIN ENTRANCES AND EXITS</data>
      <data key="d8">INDOOR CONCERT ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">In Scenario 1, participants entered and exited the indoor arena through two main entrances/exits without further restrictions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.55</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FOUR QUADRANT ENTRANCES AND EXITS" target="ARENA QUADRANTS">
      <data key="d7">FOUR QUADRANT ENTRANCES AND EXITS</data>
      <data key="d8">ARENA QUADRANTS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">In Scenario 2, participants used the entrance/exit assigned to their ticketed quadrant and were not allowed to change quadrants.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.62</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EIGHT ENTRANCES AND EXITS" target="INDOOR CONCERT ARENA">
      <data key="d7">EIGHT ENTRANCES AND EXITS</data>
      <data key="d8">INDOOR CONCERT ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">In Scenario 3, the number of arena entrances/exits was increased to eight as part of the stronger contact-reduction setup.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.5</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA" target="APPROXIMATE 1.47 ACH FRESH-AIR VENTILATION">
      <data key="d7">QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">APPROXIMATE 1.47 ACH FRESH-AIR VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The arena has an approximate fresh-air ACH of 1.47, derived from 198,000 m3 h-1 ventilation capacity divided by 135,000 m3 room volume.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA" target="AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The arena model was used as the modeled indoor environment in which aerosol distribution was simulated.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FOYER" target="TWO LONG TUNNELS">
      <data key="d7">FOYER</data>
      <data key="d8">TWO LONG TUNNELS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Visitors proceed from the foyer into two long tunnels running parallel to the arena interior, creating a direct circulation connection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INNER SPACE" target="DOWNSTREAM AIRFLOW TOWARD THE INNER SPACE">
      <data key="d7">INNER SPACE</data>
      <data key="d8">DOWNSTREAM AIRFLOW TOWARD THE INNER SPACE</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The inner arena space is the target region of the downstream airflow pattern produced by the high-level jet nozzles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TWO LONG TUNNELS" target="CORRIDORS BRANCHING OFF THE TUNNELS">
      <data key="d7">TWO LONG TUNNELS</data>
      <data key="d8">CORRIDORS BRANCHING OFF THE TUNNELS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The corridors branch off the two long tunnels, forming secondary access routes from the tunnel system.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.84</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CORRIDORS BRANCHING OFF THE TUNNELS" target="EVENT ROOM">
      <data key="d7">CORRIDORS BRANCHING OFF THE TUNNELS</data>
      <data key="d8">EVENT ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The corridors connect the tunnel system to the event room, which visitors reach through these branching routes.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="WEST AND EAST MAIN ENTRANCES" target="FOYER">
      <data key="d7">WEST AND EAST MAIN ENTRANCES</data>
      <data key="d8">FOYER</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The west and east main entrances open into the foyer at the south end of the arena, forming the usual visitor entry route before the pandemic.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EMERGENCY EXITS ON THE LONG SIDES" target="QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA">
      <data key="d7">EMERGENCY EXITS ON THE LONG SIDES</data>
      <data key="d8">QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The emergency exits on the long sides connect to the arena and were used in Scenarios 2 and 3 as additional entry and exit routes, increasing the usable entrances/exits to eight.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OUTLETS UNDER THE GRANDSTANDS" target="GRANDSTANDS">
      <data key="d7">OUTLETS UNDER THE GRANDSTANDS</data>
      <data key="d8">GRANDSTANDS</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The under-grandstand outlets connect the HVAC supply pathway to the grandstand seating zone, supporting local air delivery around spectators.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.91</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OUTLETS UNDER THE GRANDSTANDS" target="ACTUAL VENTILATION SYSTEM OF THE ARENA">
      <data key="d7">OUTLETS UNDER THE LATERAL GRANDSTANDS</data>
      <data key="d8">ACTUAL VENTILATION SYSTEM OF THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The under-grandstand outlets connect to the actual ventilation system as supply-air discharge paths.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OUTLETS UNDER THE GRANDSTANDS" target="ARENA">
      <data key="d7">OUTLETS UNDER THE LATERAL GRANDSTANDS</data>
      <data key="d8">ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The under-grandstand outlets connect the actual ventilation airflow to the arena interior, allowing supplied air to enter the occupied hall.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="JET NOZZLES ABOVE THE HEADS OF THE SPECTATORS" target="INNER SPACE">
      <data key="d7">JET NOZZLES ABOVE THE HEADS OF THE SPECTATORS</data>
      <data key="d8">INNER SPACE</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The jet nozzles connect the ventilation supply to the inner arena space by blowing air downstream toward that central interior region.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.89</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="JET NOZZLES ABOVE THE HEADS OF THE SPECTATORS" target="DOWNSTREAM AIRFLOW TOWARD THE INNER SPACE">
      <data key="d7">JET NOZZLES ABOVE THE HEADS OF THE SPECTATORS</data>
      <data key="d8">DOWNSTREAM AIRFLOW TOWARD THE INNER SPACE</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The jet nozzles create the described downstream airflow pattern toward the inner space, shaping air movement across the arena interior.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="APPROXIMATE 1.47 ACH FRESH-AIR VENTILATION" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">APPROXIMATE 1.47 ACH FRESH-AIR VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The fresh-air ACH affects airborne SARS-CoV-2 concentration by diluting and removing virus-laden aerosols from the arena air.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DOWNSTREAM AIRFLOW TOWARD THE INNER SPACE" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">DOWNSTREAM AIRFLOW TOWARD THE INNER SPACE</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">ACH_AFFECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The directed airflow pattern can affect the spatial distribution of airborne SARS-CoV-2 aerosols by transporting and diluting exhaled particles within the arena.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.66</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SEATING CAPACITY OF UP TO 8,228 PEOPLE" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">SEATING CAPACITY OF UP TO 8,228 PEOPLE</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Higher spectator occupancy can increase the aggregate respiratory aerosol and potential SARS-CoV-2 source strength because more people may emit virus-laden particles.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OCCUPIED PAIRS OF SEATS WITH 1.5 M SPACING" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">OCCUPIED PAIRS OF SEATS WITH 1.5 M SPACING</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Occupied seat pairs represent active human aerosol sources, while the 1.5 m spacing between occupied pairs reduces density compared with fully packed seating.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.69</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PARTICIPANTS AND STAFF MEMBERS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">PARTICIPANTS AND STAFF MEMBERS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence of participants and staff creates a potential source of SARS-CoV-2 introduction and respiratory aerosol generation if infected individuals are present. The described protocol reduced this occupancy-related risk through PCR testing, exclusion criteria, symptom checks, and mandatory N95 mask use.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_21</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ENTRANCE AND EXIT QUEUES OUTSIDE THE ARENA" target="EVENT ARENA">
      <data key="d7">ENTRANCE AND EXIT QUEUES OUTSIDE THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">EVENT ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The entrance and exit queues are located outside but directly associated with the arena access points. Participants pass through these adjacent areas while entering and leaving, and N95 mask use was required there as well as inside the arena.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.65</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_21</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OUTDOOR CATERING AREA" target="EVENT ARENA">
      <data key="d7">OUTDOOR CATERING AREA</data>
      <data key="d8">EVENT ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The catering service was provided outside the arena, making it an adjacent operational zone. Mask removal was permitted there only when 1.5 meters of distance could be maintained.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.55</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_21</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PARTICIPANTS INSIDE THE ARENA" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">PARTICIPANTS INSIDE THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence of participants increases the potential for SARS-CoV-2 emission and exposure in the indoor arena if any participant were infected. This relationship is conditional because the text reports no known infections during the event and describes mitigation measures such as distancing, masks, hygiene rules, and contact tracing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.58</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="40 HYGIENE STEWARDS INSIDE THE ARENA" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">40 HYGIENE STEWARDS INSIDE THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The hygiene stewards contribute to total indoor occupancy and therefore could conditionally contribute to SARS-CoV-2 emission if infected. Their main role, however, was to enforce distancing and hygiene practices, so their net relevance to pathogen risk is indirect and mitigated.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.32</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EVENT STAFF" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">EVENT STAFF</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Event staff add to the overall occupancy load and had interactions with participants during check-in and briefing, creating conditional relevance for SARS-CoV-2 exposure risk. The text also notes that staff received detailed hygiene training, which mitigates this risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.28</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EVENT PARTICIPANTS" target="AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION WITHIN THE ARENA">
      <data key="d7">EVENT PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION WITHIN THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The participants constitute the occupancy load associated with the event setting in which aerosol distribution and exposure were considered.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.55</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM" target="QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA">
      <data key="d7">COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d8">QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The complete ventilation system was included as part of the arena CFD model and represents the ventilation infrastructure serving the modeled indoor arena environment.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.82</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM" target="AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION">
      <data key="d7">COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOL DISTRIBUTION</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The ventilation system is a modeled airflow component influencing the simulated aerosol distribution pattern in the arena, though the excerpt does not quantify flow rates or air-change rates.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM" target="RBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA">
      <data key="d7">COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d8">RBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The complete ventilation system serves the modeled arena and provides the air-handling context for room air flow, CO2 transport, and aerosol transport.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM" target="STALLS">
      <data key="d7">COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d8">STALLS</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The ventilation system serves the stalls as an occupied seating zone, establishing the airflow conditions used to evaluate CO2 and aerosol movement.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.79</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM" target="STANDS">
      <data key="d7">COMPLETE VENTILATION SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d8">STANDS</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The ventilation system serves the stands as an occupied seating zone, establishing airflow conditions that were evaluated separately from the stalls.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="GRANDSTANDS AND SEATS" target="QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA">
      <data key="d7">GRANDSTANDS AND SEATS</data>
      <data key="d8">QUARTERBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">ADJACENT_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The grandstands and seats are built-in seating areas within the arena model. The valid relation set lacks a containment relation, so this indicates their spatial association with the larger modeled arena zone.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.62</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="RBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA" target="ROOM AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d7">RBACK IMMOBILIEN ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">ROOM AIR FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The arena has a modeled room-air-flow distribution pattern derived from pre-calculations and used to simulate aerosol and CO2 trajectories.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FRONT OF THE STALLS" target="ROOM AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d7">FRONT OF THE STALLS</data>
      <data key="d8">ROOM AIR FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The front of the stalls was represented as a location where infectious persons were placed to sample the local room-air-flow condition and resulting aerosol movement.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.74</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="BACK OF THE STALLS" target="ROOM AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d7">BACK OF THE STALLS</data>
      <data key="d8">ROOM AIR FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The back of the stalls was represented as a location where infectious persons were placed to sample the local room-air-flow condition and compare it with the front stall condition.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.74</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="STANDS" target="ROOM AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d7">STANDS</data>
      <data key="d8">ROOM AIR FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The stands have a room-air-flow pattern considered separately from the stalls because different air flows in the stalls and stands were recorded for the simulation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TWELVE INFECTIOUS-PERSON SEATING BLOCKS" target="ROOM AIRFLOW">
      <data key="d7">TWELVE INFECTIOUS-PERSON SEATING BLOCKS</data>
      <data key="d8">ROOM AIR FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The seating blocks containing infectious persons are within the modeled airflow field, so their source locations are interpreted relative to the room-air-flow pattern.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="4000 VIRTUAL SPECTATORS" target="CO2">
      <data key="d7">4000 VIRTUAL SPECTATORS</data>
      <data key="d8">CO2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">All 4000 virtual spectators increase the modeled CO2 load because each spectator emits breathing air containing 20 litres of CO2 per hour.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.96</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TWENTY-FOUR INFECTIOUS PERSONS" target="INFECTIOUS AEROSOLS OF 0.5, 5, AND 10 ΜM">
      <data key="d7">TWENTY-FOUR INFECTIOUS PERSONS</data>
      <data key="d8">INFECTIOUS AEROSOLS OF 0.5, 5, AND 10 ΜM</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The 24 infectious persons increase airborne infectious aerosol loading by emitting 0.5, 5, and 10 µm particles while breathing.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.97</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TWENTY-FOUR INFECTIOUS PERSONS" target="CO2">
      <data key="d7">TWENTY-FOUR INFECTIOUS PERSONS</data>
      <data key="d8">CO2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The infectious persons are part of the virtual spectator population and therefore also emit breathing air containing CO2.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.76</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SINGING, SHOUTING, OR CHEERING PARTICIPANTS" target="CO2">
      <data key="d7">SINGING, SHOUTING, OR CHEERING PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">CO2</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Singing, shouting, or cheering is assumed to increase breathing volume to 12 l min−1 per person, increasing the corresponding amount of exhaled CO2.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.87</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_27</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SINGING, SHOUTING, OR CHEERING PARTICIPANTS" target="SARS-COV-2-LADEN RESPIRATORY DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">SINGING, SHOUTING, OR CHEERING PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2-LADEN RESPIRATORY AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">When participants are infectious, elevated respiratory activity during singing, shouting, or cheering can increase aerosol emission and therefore increase virus-containing aerosol release. This is based on the stated higher breathing volume and the model’s infectious-participant aerosol source assumption.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_27</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INFECTIOUS PARTICIPANTS" target="SARS-COV-2-LADEN RESPIRATORY DROPLETS">
      <data key="d7">INFECTIOUS PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2-LADEN RESPIRATORY AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Infectious participants are modeled as sources of virus-containing exhaled aerosols, increasing airborne pathogen exposure potential in the arena.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.91</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_27</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INFECTIOUS PARTICIPANTS" target="INHALABLE INFECTIOUS AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">INFECTIOUS PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">EXHALED INFECTIOUS AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">Infectious participants increase the airborne infectious aerosol burden by exhaling aerosols into the arena.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="INFECTIOUS PARTICIPANTS" target="AFFECTED PERSONS WITH INCREASED AEROSOL EXPOSURE">
      <data key="d7">INFECTIOUS PARTICIPANTS</data>
      <data key="d8">AFFECTED PERSONS WITH INCREASED AEROSOL EXPOSURE</data>
      <data key="d9">OCCUPANCY_INCREASES</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence and seating locations of infectious participants increase the number of other participants who may become affected by elevated aerosol exposure.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VIRTUAL MOUTH RESPIRATION OPENINGS" target="ARENA">
      <data key="d7">VIRTUAL MOUTH RESPIRATION OPENINGS</data>
      <data key="d8">ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The virtual mouth openings exchange modeled respiratory air with the arena environment and provide the location where aerosol exposure is evaluated.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.78</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_27</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ACTUAL VENTILATION SYSTEM OF THE ARENA" target="ARENA">
      <data key="d7">ACTUAL VENTILATION SYSTEM OF THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The actual ventilation system serves the arena by supplying air through under-grandstand outlets and jet nozzles and extracting air through corner suction towers.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ACTUAL VENTILATION SYSTEM OF THE ARENA" target="≥3 AIR CHANGES PER HOUR">
      <data key="d7">ACTUAL VENTILATION SYSTEM OF THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">1.46 AIR CHANGES PER HOUR</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The actual ventilation system has an air exchange rate of 1.46 air changes per hour, based on a supply airflow of 198,000 m3 h-1.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MODIFIED VENTILATION SYSTEM IN THE ARENA" target="ARENA">
      <data key="d7">MODIFIED VENTILATION SYSTEM IN THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">SERVES</data>
      <data key="d10">The modified ventilation system serves the arena in the virtual scenario by reducing supply flow and extracting air through long roof-level exhaust pipes to promote displacement flow.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MODIFIED VENTILATION SYSTEM IN THE ARENA" target="≥3 AIR CHANGES PER HOUR">
      <data key="d7">MODIFIED VENTILATION SYSTEM IN THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">0.85 AIR CHANGES PER HOUR</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_ACH</data>
      <data key="d10">The modified ventilation system has an air exchange rate of 0.85 air changes per hour, based on a reduced supply airflow of 115,000 m3 h-1.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MODIFIED VENTILATION SYSTEM IN THE ARENA" target="DISPLACEMENT FLOW">
      <data key="d7">MODIFIED VENTILATION SYSTEM IN THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d8">DISPLACEMENT FLOW</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The modified ventilation system is designed to create displacement flow by using roof-level exhaust pipes and switching off jet nozzles and corner suction towers.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CORNER AIR-SUCTION TOWERS" target="ACTUAL VENTILATION SYSTEM OF THE ARENA">
      <data key="d7">CORNER AIR-SUCTION TOWERS</data>
      <data key="d8">ACTUAL VENTILATION SYSTEM OF THE ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The corner suction towers connect to the actual ventilation system as air-extraction pathways.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CORNER AIR-SUCTION TOWERS" target="ARENA">
      <data key="d7">CORNER AIR-SUCTION TOWERS</data>
      <data key="d8">ARENA</data>
      <data key="d9">CONNECTS_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The corner suction towers connect to the arena hall and remove air from the space in the actual ventilation variant.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CORNER AIR-SUCTION TOWERS" target="LARGE EDDIES">
      <data key="d7">CORNER AIR-SUCTION TOWERS</data>
      <data key="d8">LARGE EDDIES</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DISTRIBUTION_PATTERN</data>
      <data key="d10">The corner suction towers are treated as part of the airflow configuration that could contribute to large eddies; they are switched off in the modified variant to reduce such structures.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.68</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d14">0676edf9-1d10-4220-bdea-1b4729f9856d</data>
